{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qd9Cw8x4eodJHxYnXKACmV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Iteration 19 вҖ” Failure Analysis\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’## Overview\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’1 failure out of 11 real-file test cases (90.9% pass rate). This is a **regression** вҖ” \"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\" passed in iteration 18 and now fails in iteration 19. The remaining 10 real files still pass.\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’---\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’## Pattern 1: commonShort2 Expansion Admits Polish Body-Text as Candidates\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’**Affected file:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka.real.txt` (real file)\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’**Affects:** Real files only. This specific regression cannot occur in generated files because the generated template files use English OCR content.\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’---\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’### What the file contains\n    18вҶ’\n    19вҶ’```\n    20вҶ’Line 0:  SmaЕјona zielona fasolka          вҶҗ correct title (mixed-case Polish)\n    21вҶ’Line 1:  GREEN BEANS BORKEUM              вҶҗ ALL_CAPS English translation\n    22вҶ’Line 2:  к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ лі¶мқҢ                        вҶҗ Korean original\n    23вҶ’...\n    24вҶ’Line 21: No potelni rozprowadЕј oliwДҷ z oliwek i smaЕј crosnek na duzym ogr\n    25вҶ’Line 23: Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno   вҶҗ \"Serve hot or cold\" (Polish)\n    26вҶ’Line 24: 64\n    27вҶ’```\n    28вҶ’\n    29вҶ’The correct answer is `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`. The file is a bilingual recipe page: Polish title on line 0, then an ALL_CAPS English/romanization translation on line 1.\n    30вҶ’\n    31вҶ’---\n    32вҶ’\n    33вҶ’### Why iteration 18 passed\n    34вҶ’\n    35вҶ’In iteration 18, `commonShort2` contained only basic Polish prepositions (`w`, `z`). The line `Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno` contained `\"na\"` вҖ” a 2-letter lowercase word not in commonShort2. The `isLikelyGarbled` multi-word check flagged `\"na\"` as a garbled fragment, causing the entire line to be filtered by `passesHardFilters`. Only `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` (and the now-suppressed bilingual translation pair) survived as candidates, so the single-title result was correct.\n    36вҶ’\n    37вҶ’---\n    38вҶ’\n    39вҶ’### What iteration 19 changed\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’Iteration 19 added Polish prepositions to `commonShort2`:\n    42вҶ’\n    43вҶ’```typescript\n    44вҶ’\"ze\", \"bo\", \"na\", \"ni\", \"po\", \"ku\", \"od\", \"za\", \"co\",\n    45вҶ’```\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’This was intended to fix titles like `Krem Grzybowy ze ЕҡmietanД…` (Pattern 2 from iter 18). It succeeded at that. However, it has a **collateral effect**: Polish body-text lines that previously failed the garbled-word check because they contained these prepositions now pass `passesHardFilters`.\n    48вҶ’\n    49вҶ’Specifically in this file:\n    50вҶ’\n    51вҶ’- **`\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"`** (line 23, \"Serve hot or cold\"):\n    52вҶ’  In iter 18: `\"na\"` triggered `hasGarbledWord` вҶ’ filtered.\n    53вҶ’  In iter 19: `\"na\"` is in `commonShort2` вҶ’ not flagged вҶ’ **passes all hard filters**.\n    54вҶ’\n    55вҶ’- **`\"No potelni rozprowadЕј oliwДҷ z oliwek i smaЕј crosnek na duzym ogr\"`** (line 21):\n    56вҶ’  Same mechanism вҖ” `\"na\"` passes in iter 19 but would have been caught in iter 18.\n    57вҶ’\n    58вҶ’Both lines now enter the candidate pool as single-line candidates.\n    59вҶ’\n    60вҶ’---\n    61вҶ’\n    62вҶ’### Why the algorithm fails\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’The bilingual detection (unchanged between iter 18 and 19) correctly identifies `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` as a translation of `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` and suppresses it from `scoredForThreshold`. This prevents the translation's ALL_CAPS bonuses from inflating the threshold. So far so good.\n    65вҶ’\n    66вҶ’However, the newly admitted body-text candidates are **not translations** вҖ” the bilingual detection has no mechanism to identify them. They enter the scoring pool as ordinary candidates.\n    67вҶ’\n    68вҶ’The failure path is most likely through the **multi-title guard**:\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’1. After threshold filtering, `selected` contains `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` PLUS one or more body-text candidates (e.g., `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"`).\n    71вҶ’2. `allCapsSelected = selected.filter(s => isAllCaps(s.text))` = **empty** (GREEN BEANS BORKEUM was suppressed; body-text lines are mixed-case).\n    72вҶ’3. When `allCapsSelected.length === 0`, the multi-title guard takes the implicit path: **keep all candidates**.\n    73вҶ’4. Both `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` and `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` survive dedup (neither is a substring of the other).\n    74вҶ’5. Result: `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka + Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` вҖ” does not match expected `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"`.\n    75вҶ’\n    76вҶ’An alternative failure path (if embedding scores differ enough): the body-text candidate has a higher `thresholdScore` than `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"`, inflating the threshold such that the title no longer passes `s.score >= threshold`. This would produce no result (or a fallback to the wrong candidate).\n    77вҶ’\n    78вҶ’---\n    79вҶ’\n    80вҶ’### Root cause summary\n    81вҶ’\n    82вҶ’The `commonShort2` expansion fixed real title failures (Pattern 2, iter 18) but also **weakened the garbled-word filter for Polish body text**. Polish recipe instructions frequently use short prepositions (`na`, `po`, `za`, `od`). Adding them to the \"not-garbled\" whitelist correctly admits Polish title words, but also admits Polish cooking instructions as candidates.\n    83вҶ’\n    84вҶ’The bilingual detection and other filters are not designed to handle this secondary effect. The consequence is a regression in a file that was previously correctly handled.\n    85вҶ’\n    86вҶ’---\n    87вҶ’\n    88вҶ’### Why this pattern affects only real files\n    89вҶ’\n    90вҶ’Generated test files use English OCR content built from templates. The body text is English (e.g., \"Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form\"), which is filtered by `looksLikeCookingInstruction` (added in iter 19 вҖ” covering this exact scenario). Polish cooking instructions like `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` do not start with English imperative verbs, so they bypass the cooking-instruction filter. Real files are more likely to contain Polish body text of this kind.\n    91вҶ’\n    92вҶ’---\n    93вҶ’\n    94вҶ’## No Other Patterns\n    95вҶ’\n    96вҶ’Only one real file fails. There are no generated-file failures in this iteration. The single failure is fully explained by the mechanism above.\n    97вҶ’\n    98вҶ’---\n    99вҶ’\n   100вҶ’## Suggested Fix Direction\n   101вҶ’\n   102вҶ’The problem is that `commonShort2` serves a dual purpose: it whitelists short words for the garbled-word check. Expanding it for Polish titles is correct, but it inadvertently whitelists the same short words that appear in Polish body text.\n   103вҶ’\n   104вҶ’Two non-exclusive approaches:\n   105вҶ’\n   106вҶ’1. **Extend `looksLikeCookingInstruction` to cover Polish imperative verbs** вҖ” add `Podawaj`, `Dodaj`, `SmaЕј`, `Gotuj`, `OdcedЕә`, etc. to the verb list. This would filter the specific body-text lines without touching the short-word logic.\n   107вҶ’\n   108вҶ’2. **Add a position-based tiebreak for zero-ALL_CAPS multi-candidate results** вҖ” when `allCapsSelected.length === 0` and multiple mixed-case candidates survive, prefer the one at position 0 (or the earliest) rather than keeping all. The title is almost always near the top of the document; late-appearing body-text candidates should lose to position-0 candidates.\n   109вҶ’\n   110вҶ’Option 2 is the safer general fix (it doesn't require enumerating Polish cooking verbs), but either would resolve this specific regression.\n   111вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"765d8c11-d683-44d1-b1e1-90d437cce749","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/19-55b161b/feedback.md","content":"# Iteration 19 вҖ” Failure Analysis\n\n## Overview\n\n1 failure out of 11 real-file test cases (90.9% pass rate). This is a **regression** вҖ” \"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\" passed in iteration 18 and now fails in iteration 19. The remaining 10 real files still pass.\n\n---\n\n## Pattern 1: commonShort2 Expansion Admits Polish Body-Text as Candidates\n\n**Affected file:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka.real.txt` (real file)\n\n**Affects:** Real files only. This specific regression cannot occur in generated files because the generated template files use English OCR content.\n\n---\n\n### What the file contains\n\n```\nLine 0:  SmaЕјona zielona fasolka          вҶҗ correct title (mixed-case Polish)\nLine 1:  GREEN BEANS BORKEUM              вҶҗ ALL_CAPS English translation\nLine 2:  к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ лі¶мқҢ                        вҶҗ Korean original\n...\nLine 21: No potelni rozprowadЕј oliwДҷ z oliwek i smaЕј crosnek na duzym ogr\nLine 23: Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno   вҶҗ \"Serve hot or cold\" (Polish)\nLine 24: 64\n```\n\nThe correct answer is `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`. The file is a bilingual recipe page: Polish title on line 0, then an ALL_CAPS English/romanization translation on line 1.\n\n---\n\n### Why iteration 18 passed\n\nIn iteration 18, `commonShort2` contained only basic Polish prepositions (`w`, `z`). The line `Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno` contained `\"na\"` вҖ” a 2-letter lowercase word not in commonShort2. The `isLikelyGarbled` multi-word check flagged `\"na\"` as a garbled fragment, causing the entire line to be filtered by `passesHardFilters`. Only `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` (and the now-suppressed bilingual translation pair) survived as candidates, so the single-title result was correct.\n\n---\n\n### What iteration 19 changed\n\nIteration 19 added Polish prepositions to `commonShort2`:\n\n```typescript\n\"ze\", \"bo\", \"na\", \"ni\", \"po\", \"ku\", \"od\", \"za\", \"co\",\n```\n\nThis was intended to fix titles like `Krem Grzybowy ze ЕҡmietanД…` (Pattern 2 from iter 18). It succeeded at that. However, it has a **collateral effect**: Polish body-text lines that previously failed the garbled-word check because they contained these prepositions now pass `passesHardFilters`.\n\nSpecifically in this file:\n\n- **`\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"`** (line 23, \"Serve hot or cold\"):\n  In iter 18: `\"na\"` triggered `hasGarbledWord` вҶ’ filtered.\n  In iter 19: `\"na\"` is in `commonShort2` вҶ’ not flagged вҶ’ **passes all hard filters**.\n\n- **`\"No potelni rozprowadЕј oliwДҷ z oliwek i smaЕј crosnek na duzym ogr\"`** (line 21):\n  Same mechanism вҖ” `\"na\"` passes in iter 19 but would have been caught in iter 18.\n\nBoth lines now enter the candidate pool as single-line candidates.\n\n---\n\n### Why the algorithm fails\n\nThe bilingual detection (unchanged between iter 18 and 19) correctly identifies `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` as a translation of `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` and suppresses it from `scoredForThreshold`. This prevents the translation's ALL_CAPS bonuses from inflating the threshold. So far so good.\n\nHowever, the newly admitted body-text candidates are **not translations** вҖ” the bilingual detection has no mechanism to identify them. They enter the scoring pool as ordinary candidates.\n\nThe failure path is most likely through the **multi-title guard**:\n\n1. After threshold filtering, `selected` contains `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` PLUS one or more body-text candidates (e.g., `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"`).\n2. `allCapsSelected = selected.filter(s => isAllCaps(s.text))` = **empty** (GREEN BEANS BORKEUM was suppressed; body-text lines are mixed-case).\n3. When `allCapsSelected.length === 0`, the multi-title guard takes the implicit path: **keep all candidates**.\n4. Both `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` and `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` survive dedup (neither is a substring of the other).\n5. Result: `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka + Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` вҖ” does not match expected `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"`.\n\nAn alternative failure path (if embedding scores differ enough): the body-text candidate has a higher `thresholdScore` than `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"`, inflating the threshold such that the title no longer passes `s.score >= threshold`. This would produce no result (or a fallback to the wrong candidate).\n\n---\n\n### Root cause summary\n\nThe `commonShort2` expansion fixed real title failures (Pattern 2, iter 18) but also **weakened the garbled-word filter for Polish body text**. Polish recipe instructions frequently use short prepositions (`na`, `po`, `za`, `od`). Adding them to the \"not-garbled\" whitelist correctly admits Polish title words, but also admits Polish cooking instructions as candidates.\n\nThe bilingual detection and other filters are not designed to handle this secondary effect. The consequence is a regression in a file that was previously correctly handled.\n\n---\n\n### Why this pattern affects only real files\n\nGenerated test files use English OCR content built from templates. The body text is English (e.g., \"Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form\"), which is filtered by `looksLikeCookingInstruction` (added in iter 19 вҖ” covering this exact scenario). Polish cooking instructions like `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` do not start with English imperative verbs, so they bypass the cooking-instruction filter. Real files are more likely to contain Polish body text of this kind.\n\n---\n\n## No Other Patterns\n\nOnly one real file fails. There are no generated-file failures in this iteration. The single failure is fully explained by the mechanism above.\n\n---\n\n## Suggested Fix Direction\n\nThe problem is that `commonShort2` serves a dual purpose: it whitelists short words for the garbled-word check. Expanding it for Polish titles is correct, but it inadvertently whitelists the same short words that appear in Polish body text.\n\nTwo non-exclusive approaches:\n\n1. **Extend `looksLikeCookingInstruction` to cover Polish imperative verbs** вҖ” add `Podawaj`, `Dodaj`, `SmaЕј`, `Gotuj`, `OdcedЕә`, etc. to the verb list. This would filter the specific body-text lines without touching the short-word logic.\n\n2. **Add a position-based tiebreak for zero-ALL_CAPS multi-candidate results** вҖ” when `allCapsSelected.length === 0` and multiple mixed-case candidates survive, prefer the one at position 0 (or the earliest) rather than keeping all. The title is almost always near the top of the document; late-appearing body-text candidates should lose to position-0 candidates.\n\nOption 2 is the safer general fix (it doesn't require enumerating Polish cooking verbs), but either would resolve this specific regression.\n","numLines":111,"startLine":1,"totalLines":111}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SHcdtSQFpRRkeexYGWjjZc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’/**\n     2вҶ’ * Title Extraction\n     3вҶ’ * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n     4вҶ’ */\n     5вҶ’\n     6вҶ’import { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n     7вҶ’\n     8вҶ’export type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n     9вҶ’\n    10вҶ’const TITLE_REFERENCE =\n    11вҶ’  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\n    12вҶ’const HEADER_REFERENCE =\n    13вҶ’  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, skЕӮadniki, przygotowanie, sposГіb wykonania\";\n    14вҶ’const NOISE_REFERENCE =\n    15вҶ’  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’/**\n    18вҶ’ * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n    19вҶ’ */\n    20вҶ’const MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n    21вҶ’  // English\n    22вҶ’  \"cup\",\n    23вҶ’  \"cups\",\n    24вҶ’  \"tbsp\",\n    25вҶ’  \"tsp\",\n    26вҶ’  \"tablespoon\",\n    27вҶ’  \"teaspoon\",\n    28вҶ’  // \"oz\" and \"lb\" are matched with word boundaries in looksLikeIngredient\n    29вҶ’  // to avoid false positives (\"oz\" in \"mozzarella\", \"lb\" in \"albacore\")\n    30вҶ’  \"gram\",\n    31вҶ’  \"grams\",\n    32вҶ’  \"kg\",\n    33вҶ’  \"ml\",\n    34вҶ’  \"liter\",\n    35вҶ’  \"pinch\",\n    36вҶ’  \"dash\",\n    37вҶ’  \"handful\",\n    38вҶ’  // Polish\n    39вҶ’  \"ЕӮyЕјka\", \"ЕӮyЕјki\", \"ЕӮyЕјek\",           // tablespoon(s)\n    40вҶ’  \"ЕӮyЕјeczka\", \"ЕӮyЕјeczki\", \"ЕӮyЕјeczek\",   // teaspoon(s)\n    41вҶ’  \"szklanka\", \"szklanki\", \"szklanek\",    // cup(s)\n    42вҶ’  \"szczypta\",                            // pinch\n    43вҶ’  \"garЕӣДҮ\",                               // handful\n    44вҶ’  \"opakowanie\", \"opakowania\",            // package(s)\n    45вҶ’  \"plasterek\", \"plasterki\",             // slice(s)\n    46вҶ’];\n    47вҶ’\n    48вҶ’/**\n    49вҶ’ * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n    50вҶ’ */\n    51вҶ’const METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n    52вҶ’  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n    53вҶ’  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n    54вҶ’  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n    55вҶ’  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n    56вҶ’  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n    57вҶ’  // Polish serving-size patterns: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\", \"NA OKOЕҒO 1 KG\", \"DLA 4 OSГ“B\"\n    58вҶ’  /^NA\\s+(\\d|OKOЕҒO)\\b/i,\n    59вҶ’  /^DLA\\s+\\d/i,\n    60вҶ’  // OCR-resilient: \"DLA\" + any token + serving-unit word (handles DLA & OSOB, DLA В§ OSOB, etc.)\n    61вҶ’  /^DLA\\s+\\S+\\s+OSOB/i,\n    62вҶ’  // OCR-resilient: \"DLA\" + single non-alphanumeric char (common digitвҶ’symbol OCR error)\n    63вҶ’  /^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i,\n    64вҶ’  // Time-unit metadata: any line containing \"N MIN\" or \"N GODZ\" is prep/cook/rest time,\n    65вҶ’  // regardless of OCR-corrupted prefix (catches PRZYGOTOWANTE, GOTOMANTE, etc.)\n    66вҶ’  /\\b\\d+\\s*MIN\\b/i,\n    67вҶ’  /\\b\\d+\\s*GODZ/i,\n    68вҶ’  // Season/category indicators\n    69вҶ’  /^SEZON\\s*:/i,\n    70вҶ’  /^KATEGORIA\\s*:/i,\n    71вҶ’  /^RODZAJ\\s*:/i,\n    72вҶ’];\n    73вҶ’\n    74вҶ’/**\n    75вҶ’ * Single-word non-title words вҖ” standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n    76вҶ’ */\n    77вҶ’const NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n    78вҶ’  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n    79вҶ’  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n    80вҶ’  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n    81вҶ’  \"buns\", \"with\",\n    82вҶ’]);\n    83вҶ’\n    84вҶ’function looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n    85вҶ’  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n    86вҶ’  if (MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern))) return true;\n    87вҶ’  // Compact metric: \"100g\", \"50ml\", \"250g\" вҖ” digit immediately followed by g/ml/kg\n    88вҶ’  if (/\\b\\d+\\s*(?:g|ml|kg)\\b/i.test(line)) return true;\n    89вҶ’  // \"to taste\" / \"do smaku\" вҖ” qualitative ingredient with no unit\n    90вҶ’  if (/\\bto taste\\b/i.test(line) || /\\bdo smaku\\b/i.test(line)) return true;\n    91вҶ’  return false;\n    92вҶ’}\n    93вҶ’\n    94вҶ’function startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n    95вҶ’  // Match lines starting with a digit, or bullet-then-digit (e.g., \"- 2 jajka\")\n    96вҶ’  return /^\\s*(?:[-вҖў*]\\s*)?\\d/.test(line);\n    97вҶ’}\n    98вҶ’\n    99вҶ’function stripDiacritics(text: string): string {\n   100вҶ’  return text.normalize(\"NFKD\").replace(/[\\u0300-\\u036f]/g, \"\");\n   101вҶ’}\n   102вҶ’\n   103вҶ’/**\n   104вҶ’ * Known recipe section labels вҖ” these are structural headers, not recipe titles.\n   105вҶ’ * Matched case-insensitively after trimming, stripping trailing punctuation, and stripping diacritics.\n   106вҶ’ * Polish entries are stored without diacritics for OCR resilience (e.g. \"SKLADNIKI\" matches \"skЕӮadniki\").\n   107вҶ’ */\n   108вҶ’const SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n   109вҶ’  // English\n   110вҶ’  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n   111вҶ’  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n   112вҶ’  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n   113вҶ’  // Polish вҖ” recipe section labels (stored without diacritics for OCR resilience)\n   114вҶ’  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n   115вҶ’  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n   116вҶ’  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",  // ciasto = dough/pastry base (recipe-internal section AND chapter label)\n   117вҶ’  // Polish вҖ” recipe-book chapter/category labels (food groups, meal types)\n   118вҶ’  \"warzywa\",          // vegetables\n   119вҶ’  \"mieso\",            // meat (miДҷso)\n   120вҶ’  \"miesa\",            // meats (miДҷsa)\n   121вҶ’  \"ryby\",             // fish\n   122вҶ’  \"owoce morza\",      // seafood\n   123вҶ’  \"zupy\",             // soups\n   124вҶ’  \"salatki\",          // salads (saЕӮatki)\n   125вҶ’  \"desery\",           // desserts\n   126вҶ’  \"napoje\",           // drinks\n   127вҶ’  \"pieczywo\",         // bread/baked goods\n   128вҶ’  \"przekaski\",        // appetizers/snacks\n   129вҶ’  \"sniadania\",        // breakfasts (Еӣniadania)\n   130вҶ’  \"obiady\",           // dinners/lunches\n   131вҶ’  \"kolacje\",          // suppers\n   132вҶ’  \"makarony\",         // pasta dishes\n   133вҶ’  \"kasza\",            // groats/grains\n   134вҶ’  \"kasze\",            // groats/grains (plural)\n   135вҶ’  \"dania glowne\",     // main courses (dania gЕӮГіwne)\n   136вҶ’  \"przystawki\",       // starters\n   137вҶ’  \"dodatki\",          // side dishes\n   138вҶ’  \"przetwory\",        // preserves\n   139вҶ’  \"wypieki\",          // baked goods\n   140вҶ’  \"ciasta\",           // cakes (plural)\n   141вҶ’  \"ciastka\",          // cookies\n   142вҶ’  \"torty\",            // layer cakes\n   143вҶ’  \"placki\",           // pancakes/flatbreads\n   144вҶ’  \"koktajle\",         // cocktails/smoothies\n   145вҶ’]);\n   146вҶ’\n   147вҶ’function isSectionLabel(text: string): boolean {\n   148вҶ’  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n   149вҶ’  return SECTION_LABELS.has(normalized);\n   150вҶ’}\n   151вҶ’\n   152вҶ’/**\n   153вҶ’ * Recipe-internal section labels that should ALWAYS block multi-line joins,\n   154вҶ’ * even when the combined word count is вүҘ 3.\n   155вҶ’ * Category labels (\"zupy\", \"placki\", etc.) are NOT in this set вҖ” they can\n   156вҶ’ * legitimately start a multi-word recipe title like \"Zupy Zimowe Warzywne\".\n   157вҶ’ */\n   158вҶ’const ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS = new Set([\n   159вҶ’  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n   160вҶ’  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n   161вҶ’  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n   162вҶ’  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n   163вҶ’  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n   164вҶ’  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n   165вҶ’]);\n   166вҶ’\n   167вҶ’function isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(text: string): boolean {\n   168вҶ’  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n   169вҶ’  return ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS.has(normalized);\n   170вҶ’}\n   171вҶ’\n   172вҶ’function isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n   173вҶ’  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n   174вҶ’  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n   175вҶ’}\n   176вҶ’\n   177вҶ’function looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n   178вҶ’  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n   179вҶ’}\n   180вҶ’\n   181вҶ’function isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n   182вҶ’  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n   183вҶ’  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n   184вҶ’\n   185вҶ’  // Check vowel ratio вҖ” English/Polish text typically has 30вҖ“50% vowels\n   186вҶ’  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYД…ДҷГіД„ДҳГ“]/g, \"\").length;\n   187вҶ’  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n   188вҶ’  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n   189вҶ’\n   190вҶ’  // Single orphaned word вүӨ3 letters that isn't a common word\n   191вҶ’  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   192вҶ’  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n   193вҶ’    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n   194вҶ’    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n   195вҶ’    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n   196вҶ’    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n   197вҶ’  ]);\n   198вҶ’  // Count all Unicode letters (not just ASCII) so Polish words like \"Е»ur\" (3 letters) pass\n   199вҶ’  const unicodeLetters = text.trim().replace(/[^a-zA-ZД…ДҮДҷЕӮЕ„ГіЕӣЕәЕјД„ДҶДҳЕҒЕғГ“ЕҡЕ№Е»]/g, \"\");\n   200вҶ’  if (words.length === 1 && unicodeLetters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n   201вҶ’    return true;\n   202вҶ’  }\n   203вҶ’\n   204вҶ’  // Single word with internal lowercaseвҶ’uppercase transition вҖ” OCR noise (e.g., \"UuIw\", \"aBC\")\n   205вҶ’  // No recipe title uses this pattern as a standalone single-word candidate.\n   206вҶ’  if (words.length === 1 && /[a-z][A-Z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   207вҶ’    return true;\n   208вҶ’  }\n   209вҶ’\n   210вҶ’  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n   211вҶ’  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   212вҶ’    return true;\n   213вҶ’  }\n   214вҶ’\n   215вҶ’  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) вҖ” body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n   216вҶ’  const trimmed = text.trim();\n   217вҶ’  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n   218вҶ’    return true;\n   219вҶ’  }\n   220вҶ’\n   221вҶ’  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n   222вҶ’  if (words.length >= 2) {\n   223вҶ’    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n   224вҶ’      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n   225вҶ’      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n   226вҶ’      \"w\", \"z\",   // Polish prepositions (basic)\n   227вҶ’      \"ze\", \"bo\", \"na\", \"ni\", \"po\", \"ku\", \"od\", \"za\", \"co\",  // Polish prepositions (extended)\n   228вҶ’    ]);\n   229вҶ’    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n   230вҶ’      (w) =>\n   231вҶ’        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n   232вҶ’        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n   233вҶ’        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n   234вҶ’    );\n   235вҶ’    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n   236вҶ’      return true;\n   237вҶ’    }\n   238вҶ’  }\n   239вҶ’\n   240вҶ’  return false;\n   241вҶ’}\n   242вҶ’\n   243вҶ’const COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sautГ©|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form)\\b/i;\n   244вҶ’\n   245вҶ’function looksLikeCookingInstruction(text: string): boolean {\n   246вҶ’  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   247вҶ’  if (words.length < 4) return false;  // Instructions are multi-word sentences\n   248вҶ’  return COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS.test(text.trim());\n   249вҶ’}\n   250вҶ’\n   251вҶ’function passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n   252вҶ’  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n   253вҶ’  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n   254вҶ’  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n   255вҶ’  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n   256вҶ’  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n   257вҶ’  if (looksLikeCookingInstruction(text)) return false;\n   258вҶ’  // Pipe-separated lines are book category/chapter headers, not recipe titles\n   259вҶ’  if (text.includes(\" | \")) return false;\n   260вҶ’  // Slash-separated breadcrumbs (e.g., \"/ Jesien / Zupy\") are navigation, not titles\n   261вҶ’  // Only filter when 2+ slashes are present вҖ” single-slash lines like\n   262вҶ’  // \"TITLE / SUBTITLE\" are legitimate continuation-merged titles\n   263вҶ’  if ((text.match(/\\//g) || []).length >= 2) return false;\n   264вҶ’  // Bullet-list items (ingredients or instruction steps) are never titles\n   265вҶ’  if (/^\\s*[-вҖў*]\\s/.test(text)) return false;\n   266вҶ’  // Known recipe section labels are structural headers, not titles\n   267вҶ’  if (isSectionLabel(text)) return false;\n   268вҶ’  // Single-word non-title fragments\n   269вҶ’  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   270вҶ’  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n   271вҶ’  return true;\n   272вҶ’}\n   273вҶ’\n   274вҶ’/**\n   275вҶ’ * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n   276вҶ’ * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n   277вҶ’ */\n   278вҶ’function findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n   279вҶ’  let i = 0;\n   280вҶ’  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n   281вҶ’    i++;\n   282вҶ’  }\n   283вҶ’  // Skip long instruction-like prologues: if 5+ consecutive lines look like cooking instructions,\n   284вҶ’  // skip them to find the actual title region.\n   285вҶ’  if (i === 0) {\n   286вҶ’    let j = 0;\n   287вҶ’    while (j < lines.length && looksLikeCookingInstruction(lines[j].text)) {\n   288вҶ’      j++;\n   289вҶ’    }\n   290вҶ’    if (j >= 5) {\n   291вҶ’      i = j;\n   292вҶ’    }\n   293вҶ’  }\n   294вҶ’  return i;\n   295вҶ’}\n   296вҶ’\n   297вҶ’function stripParentheticalGloss(text: string): string {\n   298вҶ’  // Strip trailing English-gloss parentheticals from ALL_CAPS titles.\n   299вҶ’  // e.g. \"PIEROGI RUSKIE (Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)\" вҶ’ \"PIEROGI RUSKIE\"\n   300вҶ’  // Keep if parenthetical is ALL_CAPS (variation/subtitle in same language).\n   301вҶ’  // Keep if both base and paren are mixed-case (both are part of the title).\n   302вҶ’  const match = text.match(/^(.+?)\\s*\\(([^)]+)\\)\\s*$/);\n   303вҶ’  if (!match) return text;\n   304вҶ’  const [, base, paren] = match;\n   305вҶ’  if (isAllCaps(paren)) return text;\n   306вҶ’  if (!isAllCaps(base) && !isAllCaps(paren)) return text;\n   307вҶ’  return base.trim();\n   308вҶ’}\n   309вҶ’\n   310вҶ’function stripPageNumber(text: string): string {\n   311вҶ’  // \"34  Berry Jam\" вҶ’ \"Berry Jam\" (2+ spaces distinguishes from \"2 eggs\")\n   312вҶ’  const match = text.match(/^\\d{1,3}\\s{2,}(.+)$/);\n   313вҶ’  return match ? match[1] : text;\n   314вҶ’}\n   315вҶ’\n   316вҶ’function wordCount(text: string): number {\n   317вҶ’  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n   318вҶ’}\n   319вҶ’\n   320вҶ’/**\n   321вҶ’ * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n   322вҶ’ * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n   323вҶ’ */\n   324вҶ’export type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n   325вҶ’\n   326вҶ’function buildCandidates(\n   327вҶ’  lines: Array<string>\n   328вҶ’): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n   329вҶ’  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   330вҶ’\n   331вҶ’  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n   332вҶ’    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n   333вҶ’    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n   334вҶ’      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n   335вҶ’    }\n   336вҶ’  }\n   337вҶ’\n   338вҶ’  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n   339вҶ’\n   340вҶ’  // Pre-merge consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (OCR-fragmented headings).\n   341вҶ’  // When a sequence of 2+ ALL_CAPS lines each has вүӨ2 words and вүӨ25 chars, they are\n   342вҶ’  // almost certainly OCR fragments of a single heading. Merge them into one line so\n   343вҶ’  // the complete title enters the candidate pool without hitting the 3-line join ceiling.\n   344вҶ’  const capsCoalesced: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   345вҶ’  let ci = burstEnd;\n   346вҶ’  while (ci < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   347вҶ’    const line = nonEmptyLines[ci];\n   348вҶ’    if (\n   349вҶ’      isAllCaps(line.text) &&\n   350вҶ’      wordCount(line.text) <= 2 &&\n   351вҶ’      line.text.length <= 25 &&\n   352вҶ’      !isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n   353вҶ’      !looksLikeMetadata(line.text)\n   354вҶ’    ) {\n   355вҶ’      let merged = line.text;\n   356вҶ’      const startIndex = line.index;\n   357вҶ’      let j = ci + 1;\n   358вҶ’      while (j < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   359вҶ’        const next = nonEmptyLines[j];\n   360вҶ’        if (\n   361вҶ’          isAllCaps(next.text) &&\n   362вҶ’          wordCount(next.text) <= 2 &&\n   363вҶ’          next.text.length <= 25 &&\n   364вҶ’          !isSectionLabel(next.text) &&\n   365вҶ’          !looksLikeMetadata(next.text) &&\n   366вҶ’          (merged + \" \" + next.text).length <= 80\n   367вҶ’        ) {\n   368вҶ’          merged += \" \" + next.text;\n   369вҶ’          j++;\n   370вҶ’        } else {\n   371вҶ’          break;\n   372вҶ’        }\n   373вҶ’      }\n   374вҶ’      if (j > ci + 1) {\n   375вҶ’        capsCoalesced.push({ text: merged, index: startIndex });\n   376вҶ’        ci = j;\n   377вҶ’        continue;\n   378вҶ’      }\n   379вҶ’    }\n   380вҶ’    capsCoalesced.push(line);\n   381вҶ’    ci++;\n   382вҶ’  }\n   383вҶ’\n   384вҶ’  // Pre-merge continuation lines: a line starting with /&+:( is never a standalone title.\n   385вҶ’  // Merge it into the preceding line so the complete title enters the pool as a single candidate,\n   386вҶ’  // avoiding the fragile chain of conditions required by the downstream join survival logic.\n   387вҶ’  // Limitation: only one continuation line per preceding line is merged. Titles split across\n   388вҶ’  // three or more lines with continuation tokens (rare in practice) are not handled here вҖ”\n   389вҶ’  // the downstream 2-line and 3-line join candidates cover those cases instead.\n   390вҶ’  const mergedLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   391вҶ’  for (let i = 0; i < capsCoalesced.length; i++) {\n   392вҶ’    const line = capsCoalesced[i];\n   393вҶ’    if (i + 1 < capsCoalesced.length) {\n   394вҶ’      const nextText = capsCoalesced[i + 1].text;\n   395вҶ’      if (/^[/&+:(]/.test(nextText)) {\n   396вҶ’        mergedLines.push({ text: `${line.text} ${nextText}`, index: line.index });\n   397вҶ’        i++;\n   398вҶ’        continue;\n   399вҶ’      }\n   400вҶ’    }\n   401вҶ’    mergedLines.push(line);\n   402вҶ’  }\n   403вҶ’\n   404вҶ’  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n   405вҶ’  const seen = new Set<string>();\n   406вҶ’\n   407вҶ’  // Build a set of positions to skip: short ALL_CAPS lines immediately following metadata\n   408вҶ’  const metadataContinuationPositions = new Set<number>();\n   409вҶ’  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length - 1; i++) {\n   410вҶ’    if (looksLikeMetadata(mergedLines[i].text)) {\n   411вҶ’      const next = mergedLines[i + 1];\n   412вҶ’      if (isAllCaps(next.text) && wordCount(next.text) <= 2 && next.text.length <= 15) {\n   413вҶ’        metadataContinuationPositions.add(next.index);\n   414вҶ’      }\n   415вҶ’    }\n   416вҶ’  }\n   417вҶ’\n   418вҶ’  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n   419вҶ’    const line = mergedLines[i];\n   420вҶ’\n   421вҶ’    // Skip metadata continuation fragments\n   422вҶ’    if (metadataContinuationPositions.has(line.index)) continue;\n   423вҶ’\n   424вҶ’    // Single line вҖ” strip page-number prefixes and parenthetical glosses before scoring\n   425вҶ’    const singleText = stripParentheticalGloss(stripPageNumber(line.text));\n   426вҶ’    if (passesHardFilters(singleText)) {\n   427вҶ’      const norm = singleText.toLowerCase();\n   428вҶ’      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   429вҶ’        seen.add(norm);\n   430вҶ’        candidates.push({ text: singleText, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   431вҶ’      }\n   432вҶ’    }\n   433вҶ’\n   434вҶ’    // 2-line join вҖ” skip if first line is a section label AND join would be вүӨ2 words\n   435вҶ’    // (a section label followed by modifiers is likely a recipe title, not a category header)\n   436вҶ’    if (i + 1 < mergedLines.length) {\n   437вҶ’      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text}`;\n   438вҶ’      const shouldBlock2 = isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n   439вҶ’        (wordCount(joined2) <= 2 || isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(line.text));\n   440вҶ’      if (!shouldBlock2 && passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n   441вҶ’        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n   442вҶ’        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   443вҶ’          seen.add(norm);\n   444вҶ’          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n   445вҶ’        }\n   446вҶ’      }\n   447вҶ’    }\n   448вҶ’\n   449вҶ’    // 3-line join вҖ” skip if first line is a section label AND join would be вүӨ2 words\n   450вҶ’    if (i + 2 < mergedLines.length) {\n   451вҶ’      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text} ${mergedLines[i + 2].text}`;\n   452вҶ’      const shouldBlock3 = isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n   453вҶ’        (wordCount(joined3) <= 2 || isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(line.text));\n   454вҶ’      if (!shouldBlock3 && passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n   455вҶ’        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n   456вҶ’        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   457вҶ’          seen.add(norm);\n   458вҶ’          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n   459вҶ’        }\n   460вҶ’      }\n   461вҶ’    }\n   462вҶ’  }\n   463вҶ’\n   464вҶ’  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n   465вҶ’  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n   466вҶ’  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n   467вҶ’    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n   468вҶ’      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   469вҶ’      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   470вҶ’      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n   471вҶ’      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   472вҶ’      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   473вҶ’      return aShort - bShort;\n   474вҶ’    });\n   475вҶ’    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n   476вҶ’  }\n   477вҶ’\n   478вҶ’  return candidates;\n   479вҶ’}\n   480вҶ’\n   481вҶ’// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\n   482вҶ’let cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   483вҶ’let cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   484вҶ’let cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   485вҶ’\n   486вҶ’export function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n   487вҶ’  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n   488вҶ’  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n   489вҶ’  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n   490вҶ’}\n   491вҶ’\n   492вҶ’export async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n   493вҶ’  text: string,\n   494вҶ’  embed: EmbedFn\n   495вҶ’): Promise<string | undefined> {\n   496вҶ’  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   497вҶ’    return undefined;\n   498вҶ’  }\n   499вҶ’\n   500вҶ’  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n   501вҶ’  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n   502вҶ’\n   503вҶ’  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n   504вҶ’    return undefined;\n   505вҶ’  }\n   506вҶ’\n   507вҶ’  // Cache reference embeddings\n   508вҶ’  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n   509вҶ’    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n   510вҶ’  }\n   511вҶ’  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n   512вҶ’    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n   513вҶ’  }\n   514вҶ’  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n   515вҶ’    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n   516вҶ’  }\n   517вҶ’\n   518вҶ’  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with вүҘ2 words where every significant word has вүҘ4 alpha letters.\n   519вҶ’  // Insignificant tokens (вүӨ1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n   520вҶ’  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n   521вҶ’  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n   522вҶ’    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n   523вҶ’    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n   524вҶ’    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   525вҶ’  };\n   526вҶ’\n   527вҶ’  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n   528вҶ’  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n   529вҶ’  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n   530вҶ’    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n   531вҶ’    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n   532вҶ’    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n   533вҶ’    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n   534вҶ’    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n   535вҶ’    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n   536вҶ’  }\n   537вҶ’\n   538вҶ’  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n   539вҶ’  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n   540вҶ’  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n   541вҶ’\n   542вҶ’  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n   543вҶ’  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n   544вҶ’  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n   545вҶ’    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   546вҶ’    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n   547вҶ’      if (other === sc) continue;\n   548вҶ’      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   549вҶ’      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n   550вҶ’        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n   551вҶ’      );\n   552вҶ’      if (hasTruncation) {\n   553вҶ’        sc.rawScore = -1.0;  // Hard disqualification вҖ” truncated OCR artifact\n   554вҶ’        break;\n   555вҶ’      }\n   556вҶ’    }\n   557вҶ’  }\n   558вҶ’\n   559вҶ’  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n   560вҶ’    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => {\n   561вҶ’        const scoreDiff = a.rawScore - b.rawScore;\n   562вҶ’        if (Math.abs(scoreDiff) > 0.03) return scoreDiff > 0 ? a : b;\n   563вҶ’        // Tiebreak: single-line origin beats multi-line joins (avoids conflating two separate headings)\n   564вҶ’        if (a.origin === \"single\" && b.origin !== \"single\") return a;\n   565вҶ’        if (b.origin === \"single\" && a.origin !== \"single\") return b;\n   566вҶ’        // Tiebreak: more words (more specific) вҶ’ better\n   567вҶ’        const wcDiff = wordCount(b.text) - wordCount(a.text);\n   568вҶ’        if (wcDiff !== 0) return wcDiff > 0 ? b : a;\n   569вҶ’        // Tiebreak: earlier position вҶ’ better\n   570вҶ’        return a.position < b.position ? a : b;\n   571вҶ’      })\n   572вҶ’    : null;\n   573вҶ’  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n   574вҶ’\n   575вҶ’  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n   576вҶ’  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n   577вҶ’  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n   578вҶ’  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n   579вҶ’  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n   580вҶ’  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n   581вҶ’  let firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n   582вҶ’    rawScored.find((c) => {\n   583вҶ’      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n   584вҶ’      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   585вҶ’      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n   586вҶ’      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n   587вҶ’    }) ?? baseHeading\n   588вҶ’  );\n   589вҶ’\n   590вҶ’  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   591вҶ’  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n   592вҶ’    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker вҖ” amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n   593вҶ’    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n   594вҶ’    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n   595вҶ’      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n   596вҶ’      : 1.0;\n   597вҶ’\n   598вҶ’    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings.\n   599вҶ’    // Single-word ALL_CAPS terms are overwhelmingly section/category labels, not recipe titles;\n   600вҶ’    // real recipe titles in ALL_CAPS are almost always multi-word. Reduce the bonus for single words.\n   601вҶ’    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   602вҶ’      ? (wordCount(rs.text) >= 2 ? 0.08 : 0.03)\n   603вҶ’      : 0;\n   604вҶ’\n   605вҶ’    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n   606вҶ’    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   607вҶ’\n   608вҶ’    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n   609вҶ’    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n   610вҶ’    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   611вҶ’    // baseScore excludes position factor вҖ” used for diagnostics and ranking\n   612вҶ’    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   613вҶ’    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   614вҶ’    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   615вҶ’  });\n   616вҶ’\n   617вҶ’  if (scored.length === 0) {\n   618вҶ’    return undefined;\n   619вҶ’  }\n   620вҶ’\n   621вҶ’  // --- Pre-threshold bilingual title detection ---\n   622вҶ’  // When a mixed-case candidate at position 0 is followed by an ALL_CAPS candidate\n   623вҶ’  // at position вүӨ 2 that is semantically similar to it, this is a bilingual recipe\n   624вҶ’  // page (e.g., Polish title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization). Suppress confirmed\n   625вҶ’  // translation candidates before computing threshold so their bonuses don't inflate\n   626вҶ’  // the threshold beyond the mixed-case title's reach.\n   627вҶ’  // Note: we check position вүӨ 2 (local proximity), not global ALL_CAPS count, so\n   628вҶ’  // section headers later in the document (SKЕҒADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc.) are irrelevant.\n   629вҶ’  let translationCandidates: typeof scored = [];\n   630вҶ’  let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n   631вҶ’  const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n   632вҶ’  if (prePos0) {\n   633вҶ’    const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n   634вҶ’      (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2 && s.origin === \"single\"\n   635вҶ’    );\n   636вҶ’    const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n   637вҶ’\n   638вҶ’    // Method 1: embedding similarity (works for related languages)\n   639вҶ’    if (pos0Embedding && nearbyAllCaps.length > 0) {\n   640вҶ’      translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n   641вҶ’        const capEmbedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === cap.text)?.embedding;\n   642вҶ’        if (!capEmbedding) return false;\n   643вҶ’        return cosineSimilarity(pos0Embedding, capEmbedding) > 0.4;\n   644вҶ’      });\n   645вҶ’    }\n   646вҶ’\n   647вҶ’    // Method 2: layout-based detection (cross-lingual fallback).\n   648вҶ’    // When embedding similarity is insufficient (e.g. Polish вҶ” Korean romanization),\n   649вҶ’    // detect bilingual layout by position and word overlap:\n   650вҶ’    // mixed-case вүҘ2 words at pos 0 + ALL_CAPS вүҘ2 words at pos 1-2 with no shared words.\n   651вҶ’    if (translationCandidates.length === 0 && wordCount(prePos0.text) >= 2) {\n   652вҶ’      const pos0Words = new Set(\n   653вҶ’        prePos0.text.toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 2)\n   654вҶ’      );\n   655вҶ’      translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n   656вҶ’        if (wordCount(cap.text) < 2) return false;\n   657вҶ’        const capWords = cap.text.toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 2);\n   658вҶ’        return !capWords.some((w) => pos0Words.has(w));\n   659вҶ’      });\n   660вҶ’    }\n   661вҶ’\n   662вҶ’    if (translationCandidates.length > 0) {\n   663вҶ’      // Suppress standalone translations and any multi-line joins that embed the translation\n   664вҶ’      // as a suffix or substring (e.g. \"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" ends with\n   665вҶ’      // the translation; \"Title GREEN BEANS BORKEUM к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ\" includes it as a substring).\n   666вҶ’      scoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n   667вҶ’        const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   668вҶ’        return !translationCandidates.some((t) => {\n   669вҶ’          const tLower = t.text.toLowerCase();\n   670вҶ’          return sLower.startsWith(tLower) ||\n   671вҶ’                 sLower.endsWith(\" \" + tLower) ||\n   672вҶ’                 sLower.includes(\" \" + tLower);\n   673вҶ’        });\n   674вҶ’      });\n   675вҶ’    }\n   676вҶ’  }\n   677вҶ’\n   678вҶ’  // Fix 2: If the structural heading was identified as a bilingual translation, reassign it.\n   679вҶ’  // This prevents the translation's ALL_CAPS bonus from inflating the threshold and ensures\n   680вҶ’  // the fallback path in scored also uses the correct heading.\n   681вҶ’  if (\n   682вҶ’    translationCandidates.length > 0 &&\n   683вҶ’    firstStructuralHeading &&\n   684вҶ’    translationCandidates.some((t) => t.text === firstStructuralHeading!.text)\n   685вҶ’  ) {\n   686вҶ’    const nonTranslationStructural = structuralCandidates.filter(\n   687вҶ’      (sc) => !translationCandidates.some((t) => t.text === sc.text)\n   688вҶ’    );\n   689вҶ’    const newHeading = nonTranslationStructural.length > 0\n   690вҶ’      ? nonTranslationStructural.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n   691вҶ’      : undefined;\n   692вҶ’\n   693вҶ’    // Patch scored array: remove old structural bonus, apply new one\n   694вҶ’    for (const s of scored) {\n   695вҶ’      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) {\n   696вҶ’        s.score -= 0.10;\n   697вҶ’        s.baseScore -= 0.10;\n   698вҶ’      }\n   699вҶ’      if (newHeading && s.text === newHeading.text) {\n   700вҶ’        s.score += 0.10;\n   701вҶ’        s.baseScore += 0.10;\n   702вҶ’      }\n   703вҶ’    }\n   704вҶ’    // Update reference for downstream prefix-removal logic\n   705вҶ’    firstStructuralHeading = newHeading ?? undefined;\n   706вҶ’  }\n   707вҶ’\n   708вҶ’  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n   709вҶ’  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n   710вҶ’  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n   711вҶ’  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n   712вҶ’\n   713вҶ’  // Filter candidates above threshold\n   714вҶ’  let selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n   715вҶ’\n   716вҶ’  // Empty-pool fallback: when threshold filtering discards every candidate,\n   717вҶ’  // the hard filters' structural verdict should not be overruled by weak\n   718вҶ’  // embedding differentiation. Return the best positional candidate.\n   719вҶ’  if (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n   720вҶ’    const fallback = scored\n   721вҶ’      .slice()\n   722вҶ’      .sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n   723вҶ’    selected = [fallback[0]];\n   724вҶ’  }\n   725вҶ’\n   726вҶ’  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n   727вҶ’  // the threshold. Cases:\n   728вҶ’  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n   729вҶ’  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n   730вҶ’  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n   731вҶ’  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n   732вҶ’  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n   733вҶ’  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n   734вҶ’    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   735вҶ’    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   736вҶ’      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n   737вҶ’      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   738вҶ’      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n   739вҶ’      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n   740вҶ’    });\n   741вҶ’  }\n   742вҶ’\n   743вҶ’  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join (2-line or 3-line) survived the threshold\n   744вҶ’  // and its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix/suffix\n   745вҶ’  // so the dedup \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n   746вҶ’  // Note: the pre-merge step above already handles the common Baked Eggs case (&/continuation\n   747вҶ’  // on next line) by turning it into a single candidate вҖ” this block covers the rarer case where\n   748вҶ’  // a continuation-character join was generated as a 2-line/3-line candidate and the prefix\n   749вҶ’  // single also survived threshold independently (e.g. from a different code path or OCR layout).\n   750вҶ’  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( вҖ” digit continuations\n   751вҶ’  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mД…ki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n   752вҶ’  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n   753вҶ’  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n   754вҶ’    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   755вҶ’      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n   756вҶ’      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   757вҶ’      // Remove PREFIX singles whose continuation join also survived\n   758вҶ’      const isPrefixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   759вҶ’        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   760вҶ’        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n   761вҶ’        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n   762вҶ’        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n   763вҶ’      });\n   764вҶ’      if (isPrefixOfJoin) return false;\n   765вҶ’      // Remove SUFFIX singles (e.g. \"& Coriander\") whose parent join also survived\n   766вҶ’      const isSuffixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   767вҶ’        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   768вҶ’        if (!jLower.endsWith(\" \" + sLower)) return false;\n   769вҶ’        // Only remove if the suffix starts with a continuation character\n   770вҶ’        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(sLower);\n   771вҶ’      });\n   772вҶ’      if (isSuffixOfJoin) return false;\n   773вҶ’      return true;\n   774вҶ’    });\n   775вҶ’  }\n   776вҶ’\n   777вҶ’  // Pre-dedup: remove sub-section headers that are substrings of other surviving candidates.\n   778вҶ’  // A sub-section header is an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by ingredient-like lines in the source.\n   779вҶ’  // Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (bread section header, followed by \"500 g mД…ki\") is a substring of\n   780вҶ’  // \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (the real title). Without this filter, dedup kills the title.\n   781вҶ’  selected = selected.filter((candidate) => {\n   782вҶ’    if (!isAllCaps(candidate.text)) return true;\n   783вҶ’    // Check if this candidate is immediately followed by ingredient-like content\n   784вҶ’    const nextSourceLines = lines.slice(candidate.position + 1, candidate.position + 2);\n   785вҶ’    const followedByIngredients = nextSourceLines.some(\n   786вҶ’      (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || startsWithNumber(l.trim())\n   787вҶ’    );\n   788вҶ’    if (!followedByIngredients) return true;\n   789вҶ’    // Only remove if a longer candidate contains this one as a substring\n   790вҶ’    const candidateLower = candidate.text.toLowerCase();\n   791вҶ’    const hasLongerParent = rawScored.some(\n   792вҶ’      (other) =>\n   793вҶ’        other.text !== candidate.text &&\n   794вҶ’        other.text.length > candidate.text.length &&\n   795вҶ’        other.text.toLowerCase().includes(candidateLower)\n   796вҶ’    );\n   797вҶ’    return !hasLongerParent;\n   798вҶ’  });\n   799вҶ’\n   800вҶ’  // Protect multi-line joins from being destroyed by their own component singles.\n   801вҶ’  // When \"Lamb Stew\" (2-line join) survives AND both \"Lamb\" and \"Stew\" (singles) also survive,\n   802вҶ’  // the join is the intended title вҖ” remove the singles.\n   803вҶ’  const joinsToProtect = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n   804вҶ’  if (joinsToProtect.length > 0) {\n   805вҶ’    const singlesToRemove = new Set<string>();\n   806вҶ’    for (const join of joinsToProtect) {\n   807вҶ’      const joinWords = join.text.split(/\\s+/);\n   808вҶ’      const componentSingles = selected.filter(\n   809вҶ’        (s) => s.origin === \"single\" && joinWords.some((w) => s.text.toLowerCase() === w.toLowerCase())\n   810вҶ’      );\n   811вҶ’      if (componentSingles.length >= Math.min(joinWords.length, 2)) {\n   812вҶ’        componentSingles.forEach((s) => singlesToRemove.add(s.text));\n   813вҶ’      }\n   814вҶ’    }\n   815вҶ’    if (singlesToRemove.size > 0) {\n   816вҶ’      selected = selected.filter((s) => s.origin !== \"single\" || !singlesToRemove.has(s.text));\n   817вҶ’    }\n   818вҶ’  }\n   819вҶ’\n   820вҶ’  // Protect position-0 compound titles from distant sub-section headers.\n   821вҶ’  // When a position-0 compound title is longer and contains a shorter candidate\n   822вҶ’  // that appears > 10 lines later, remove the distant candidate so the dedup\n   823вҶ’  // (shorter-wins rule) doesn't destroy the compound title.\n   824вҶ’  const pos0Compounds = selected.filter((s) => s.position === 0);\n   825вҶ’  if (pos0Compounds.length > 0) {\n   826вҶ’    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   827вҶ’      if (s.position === 0) return true;\n   828вҶ’      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   829вҶ’      return !pos0Compounds.some(\n   830вҶ’        (p0) =>\n   831вҶ’          p0.position + 10 < s.position &&\n   832вҶ’          s.text.length < p0.text.length &&\n   833вҶ’          p0.text.toLowerCase().includes(sLower)\n   834вҶ’      );\n   835вҶ’    });\n   836вҶ’  }\n   837вҶ’\n   838вҶ’  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n   839вҶ’  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC вҖ” it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n   840вҶ’  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mД…ki 3 ziemniaki\".\n   841вҶ’  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n   842вҶ’  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n   843вҶ’  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n   844вҶ’    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n   845вҶ’    return !selected.some(\n   846вҶ’      (b) =>\n   847вҶ’        b !== a &&\n   848вҶ’        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n   849вҶ’        b.text.length < a.text.length\n   850вҶ’    );\n   851вҶ’  });\n   852вҶ’\n   853вҶ’  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n   854вҶ’  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (вүҘ2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n   855вҶ’  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page вҖ”\n   856вҶ’  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n   857вҶ’  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors вҶ’ mixed-case multi-title page вҶ’ keep all.\n   858вҶ’  if (selected.length > 1) {\n   859вҶ’    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n   860вҶ’    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n   861вҶ’      // Check whether non-first ALL_CAPS headings are section headers within one recipe\n   862вҶ’      // (followed immediately by ingredient-like content) rather than separate recipe titles.\n   863вҶ’      // A multi-recipe page has body text between titles; a single-recipe page has\n   864вҶ’      // ingredient lines immediately after each section heading.\n   865вҶ’      const sortedCaps = [...allCapsSelected].sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n   866вҶ’      const isSubHeader = sortedCaps.slice(1).every((cap) => {\n   867вҶ’        const nextLines = lines.slice(cap.position + 1, cap.position + 3);\n   868вҶ’        return nextLines.some(\n   869вҶ’          (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || /^\\s*\\d/.test(l.trim())\n   870вҶ’        );\n   871вҶ’      });\n   872вҶ’      if (isSubHeader) {\n   873вҶ’        selected = [sortedCaps[0]];\n   874вҶ’      } else {\n   875вҶ’        selected = allCapsSelected;\n   876вҶ’      }\n   877вҶ’    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   878вҶ’      const theCapCandidate = allCapsSelected[0];\n   879вҶ’      // Use non-empty line count so the 75% threshold is consistent regardless of blank-line density.\n   880вҶ’      const nonEmptyCount = lines.filter((l) => l.trim().length > 0).length;\n   881вҶ’      const capRelPos = theCapCandidate.position / Math.max(nonEmptyCount, 1);\n   882вҶ’      // If the sole ALL_CAPS candidate is in the last 25% of the document,\n   883вҶ’      // it's likely a category footer, not a title. Prefer the best earlier candidate.\n   884вҶ’      if (capRelPos > 0.75) {\n   885вҶ’        const earlierCandidates = selected.filter(\n   886вҶ’          (s) => s.position / Math.max(nonEmptyCount, 1) <= 0.75\n   887вҶ’        );\n   888вҶ’        if (earlierCandidates.length > 0) {\n   889вҶ’          selected = [earlierCandidates.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   890вҶ’        } else {\n   891вҶ’          // All candidates are in the last 25% вҖ” no positional basis to prefer one over another;\n   892вҶ’          // fall back to score, accepting that the guard cannot help here.\n   893вҶ’          selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   894вҶ’        }\n   895вҶ’      } else {\n   896вҶ’        selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   897вҶ’      }\n   898вҶ’    }\n   899вҶ’  }\n   900вҶ’\n   901вҶ’  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n   902вҶ’  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n   903вҶ’  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n   904вҶ’\n   905вҶ’  if (selected.length === 0) {\n   906вҶ’    return undefined;\n   907вҶ’  }\n   908вҶ’\n   909вҶ’  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n   910вҶ’}\n   911вҶ’\n   912вҶ’/**\n   913вҶ’ * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n   914вҶ’ */\n   915вҶ’export function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n   916вҶ’  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   917вҶ’    return undefined;\n   918вҶ’  }\n   919вҶ’\n   920вҶ’  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n   921вҶ’\n   922вҶ’  for (const line of lines) {\n   923вҶ’    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n   924вҶ’    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n   925вҶ’    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n   926вҶ’    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n   927вҶ’    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n   928вҶ’    return line;\n   929вҶ’  }\n   930вҶ’\n   931вҶ’  return undefined;\n   932вҶ’}\n   933вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"055ac889-8dc0-44ed-8204-6b963eb6d7a2","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"/**\n * Title Extraction\n * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n */\n\nimport { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n\nexport type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n\nconst TITLE_REFERENCE =\n  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\nconst HEADER_REFERENCE =\n  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, skЕӮadniki, przygotowanie, sposГіb wykonania\";\nconst NOISE_REFERENCE =\n  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n\n/**\n * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n */\nconst MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n  // English\n  \"cup\",\n  \"cups\",\n  \"tbsp\",\n  \"tsp\",\n  \"tablespoon\",\n  \"teaspoon\",\n  // \"oz\" and \"lb\" are matched with word boundaries in looksLikeIngredient\n  // to avoid false positives (\"oz\" in \"mozzarella\", \"lb\" in \"albacore\")\n  \"gram\",\n  \"grams\",\n  \"kg\",\n  \"ml\",\n  \"liter\",\n  \"pinch\",\n  \"dash\",\n  \"handful\",\n  // Polish\n  \"ЕӮyЕјka\", \"ЕӮyЕјki\", \"ЕӮyЕјek\",           // tablespoon(s)\n  \"ЕӮyЕјeczka\", \"ЕӮyЕјeczki\", \"ЕӮyЕјeczek\",   // teaspoon(s)\n  \"szklanka\", \"szklanki\", \"szklanek\",    // cup(s)\n  \"szczypta\",                            // pinch\n  \"garЕӣДҮ\",                               // handful\n  \"opakowanie\", \"opakowania\",            // package(s)\n  \"plasterek\", \"plasterki\",             // slice(s)\n];\n\n/**\n * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n */\nconst METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n  // Polish serving-size patterns: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\", \"NA OKOЕҒO 1 KG\", \"DLA 4 OSГ“B\"\n  /^NA\\s+(\\d|OKOЕҒO)\\b/i,\n  /^DLA\\s+\\d/i,\n  // OCR-resilient: \"DLA\" + any token + serving-unit word (handles DLA & OSOB, DLA В§ OSOB, etc.)\n  /^DLA\\s+\\S+\\s+OSOB/i,\n  // OCR-resilient: \"DLA\" + single non-alphanumeric char (common digitвҶ’symbol OCR error)\n  /^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i,\n  // Time-unit metadata: any line containing \"N MIN\" or \"N GODZ\" is prep/cook/rest time,\n  // regardless of OCR-corrupted prefix (catches PRZYGOTOWANTE, GOTOMANTE, etc.)\n  /\\b\\d+\\s*MIN\\b/i,\n  /\\b\\d+\\s*GODZ/i,\n  // Season/category indicators\n  /^SEZON\\s*:/i,\n  /^KATEGORIA\\s*:/i,\n  /^RODZAJ\\s*:/i,\n];\n\n/**\n * Single-word non-title words вҖ” standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n */\nconst NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  \"buns\", \"with\",\n]);\n\nfunction looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n  if (MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern))) return true;\n  // Compact metric: \"100g\", \"50ml\", \"250g\" вҖ” digit immediately followed by g/ml/kg\n  if (/\\b\\d+\\s*(?:g|ml|kg)\\b/i.test(line)) return true;\n  // \"to taste\" / \"do smaku\" вҖ” qualitative ingredient with no unit\n  if (/\\bto taste\\b/i.test(line) || /\\bdo smaku\\b/i.test(line)) return true;\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n  // Match lines starting with a digit, or bullet-then-digit (e.g., \"- 2 jajka\")\n  return /^\\s*(?:[-вҖў*]\\s*)?\\d/.test(line);\n}\n\nfunction stripDiacritics(text: string): string {\n  return text.normalize(\"NFKD\").replace(/[\\u0300-\\u036f]/g, \"\");\n}\n\n/**\n * Known recipe section labels вҖ” these are structural headers, not recipe titles.\n * Matched case-insensitively after trimming, stripping trailing punctuation, and stripping diacritics.\n * Polish entries are stored without diacritics for OCR resilience (e.g. \"SKLADNIKI\" matches \"skЕӮadniki\").\n */\nconst SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n  // English\n  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n  // Polish вҖ” recipe section labels (stored without diacritics for OCR resilience)\n  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",  // ciasto = dough/pastry base (recipe-internal section AND chapter label)\n  // Polish вҖ” recipe-book chapter/category labels (food groups, meal types)\n  \"warzywa\",          // vegetables\n  \"mieso\",            // meat (miДҷso)\n  \"miesa\",            // meats (miДҷsa)\n  \"ryby\",             // fish\n  \"owoce morza\",      // seafood\n  \"zupy\",             // soups\n  \"salatki\",          // salads (saЕӮatki)\n  \"desery\",           // desserts\n  \"napoje\",           // drinks\n  \"pieczywo\",         // bread/baked goods\n  \"przekaski\",        // appetizers/snacks\n  \"sniadania\",        // breakfasts (Еӣniadania)\n  \"obiady\",           // dinners/lunches\n  \"kolacje\",          // suppers\n  \"makarony\",         // pasta dishes\n  \"kasza\",            // groats/grains\n  \"kasze\",            // groats/grains (plural)\n  \"dania glowne\",     // main courses (dania gЕӮГіwne)\n  \"przystawki\",       // starters\n  \"dodatki\",          // side dishes\n  \"przetwory\",        // preserves\n  \"wypieki\",          // baked goods\n  \"ciasta\",           // cakes (plural)\n  \"ciastka\",          // cookies\n  \"torty\",            // layer cakes\n  \"placki\",           // pancakes/flatbreads\n  \"koktajle\",         // cocktails/smoothies\n]);\n\nfunction isSectionLabel(text: string): boolean {\n  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n  return SECTION_LABELS.has(normalized);\n}\n\n/**\n * Recipe-internal section labels that should ALWAYS block multi-line joins,\n * even when the combined word count is вүҘ 3.\n * Category labels (\"zupy\", \"placki\", etc.) are NOT in this set вҖ” they can\n * legitimately start a multi-word recipe title like \"Zupy Zimowe Warzywne\".\n */\nconst ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS = new Set([\n  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n]);\n\nfunction isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(text: string): boolean {\n  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n  return ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS.has(normalized);\n}\n\nfunction isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n}\n\nfunction looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n}\n\nfunction isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n\n  // Check vowel ratio вҖ” English/Polish text typically has 30вҖ“50% vowels\n  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYД…ДҷГіД„ДҳГ“]/g, \"\").length;\n  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n\n  // Single orphaned word вүӨ3 letters that isn't a common word\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  ]);\n  // Count all Unicode letters (not just ASCII) so Polish words like \"Е»ur\" (3 letters) pass\n  const unicodeLetters = text.trim().replace(/[^a-zA-ZД…ДҮДҷЕӮЕ„ГіЕӣЕәЕјД„ДҶДҳЕҒЕғГ“ЕҡЕ№Е»]/g, \"\");\n  if (words.length === 1 && unicodeLetters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Single word with internal lowercaseвҶ’uppercase transition вҖ” OCR noise (e.g., \"UuIw\", \"aBC\")\n  // No recipe title uses this pattern as a standalone single-word candidate.\n  if (words.length === 1 && /[a-z][A-Z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) вҖ” body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n  const trimmed = text.trim();\n  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n  if (words.length >= 2) {\n    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n      \"w\", \"z\",   // Polish prepositions (basic)\n      \"ze\", \"bo\", \"na\", \"ni\", \"po\", \"ku\", \"od\", \"za\", \"co\",  // Polish prepositions (extended)\n    ]);\n    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n      (w) =>\n        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n    );\n    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n      return true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\n\nconst COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sautГ©|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form)\\b/i;\n\nfunction looksLikeCookingInstruction(text: string): boolean {\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (words.length < 4) return false;  // Instructions are multi-word sentences\n  return COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS.test(text.trim());\n}\n\nfunction passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeCookingInstruction(text)) return false;\n  // Pipe-separated lines are book category/chapter headers, not recipe titles\n  if (text.includes(\" | \")) return false;\n  // Slash-separated breadcrumbs (e.g., \"/ Jesien / Zupy\") are navigation, not titles\n  // Only filter when 2+ slashes are present вҖ” single-slash lines like\n  // \"TITLE / SUBTITLE\" are legitimate continuation-merged titles\n  if ((text.match(/\\//g) || []).length >= 2) return false;\n  // Bullet-list items (ingredients or instruction steps) are never titles\n  if (/^\\s*[-вҖў*]\\s/.test(text)) return false;\n  // Known recipe section labels are structural headers, not titles\n  if (isSectionLabel(text)) return false;\n  // Single-word non-title fragments\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n  return true;\n}\n\n/**\n * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n */\nfunction findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n  let i = 0;\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n    i++;\n  }\n  // Skip long instruction-like prologues: if 5+ consecutive lines look like cooking instructions,\n  // skip them to find the actual title region.\n  if (i === 0) {\n    let j = 0;\n    while (j < lines.length && looksLikeCookingInstruction(lines[j].text)) {\n      j++;\n    }\n    if (j >= 5) {\n      i = j;\n    }\n  }\n  return i;\n}\n\nfunction stripParentheticalGloss(text: string): string {\n  // Strip trailing English-gloss parentheticals from ALL_CAPS titles.\n  // e.g. \"PIEROGI RUSKIE (Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)\" вҶ’ \"PIEROGI RUSKIE\"\n  // Keep if parenthetical is ALL_CAPS (variation/subtitle in same language).\n  // Keep if both base and paren are mixed-case (both are part of the title).\n  const match = text.match(/^(.+?)\\s*\\(([^)]+)\\)\\s*$/);\n  if (!match) return text;\n  const [, base, paren] = match;\n  if (isAllCaps(paren)) return text;\n  if (!isAllCaps(base) && !isAllCaps(paren)) return text;\n  return base.trim();\n}\n\nfunction stripPageNumber(text: string): string {\n  // \"34  Berry Jam\" вҶ’ \"Berry Jam\" (2+ spaces distinguishes from \"2 eggs\")\n  const match = text.match(/^\\d{1,3}\\s{2,}(.+)$/);\n  return match ? match[1] : text;\n}\n\nfunction wordCount(text: string): number {\n  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n}\n\n/**\n * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n */\nexport type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n\nfunction buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n\n  // Pre-merge consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (OCR-fragmented headings).\n  // When a sequence of 2+ ALL_CAPS lines each has вүӨ2 words and вүӨ25 chars, they are\n  // almost certainly OCR fragments of a single heading. Merge them into one line so\n  // the complete title enters the candidate pool without hitting the 3-line join ceiling.\n  const capsCoalesced: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n  let ci = burstEnd;\n  while (ci < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n    const line = nonEmptyLines[ci];\n    if (\n      isAllCaps(line.text) &&\n      wordCount(line.text) <= 2 &&\n      line.text.length <= 25 &&\n      !isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n      !looksLikeMetadata(line.text)\n    ) {\n      let merged = line.text;\n      const startIndex = line.index;\n      let j = ci + 1;\n      while (j < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n        const next = nonEmptyLines[j];\n        if (\n          isAllCaps(next.text) &&\n          wordCount(next.text) <= 2 &&\n          next.text.length <= 25 &&\n          !isSectionLabel(next.text) &&\n          !looksLikeMetadata(next.text) &&\n          (merged + \" \" + next.text).length <= 80\n        ) {\n          merged += \" \" + next.text;\n          j++;\n        } else {\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n      if (j > ci + 1) {\n        capsCoalesced.push({ text: merged, index: startIndex });\n        ci = j;\n        continue;\n      }\n    }\n    capsCoalesced.push(line);\n    ci++;\n  }\n\n  // Pre-merge continuation lines: a line starting with /&+:( is never a standalone title.\n  // Merge it into the preceding line so the complete title enters the pool as a single candidate,\n  // avoiding the fragile chain of conditions required by the downstream join survival logic.\n  // Limitation: only one continuation line per preceding line is merged. Titles split across\n  // three or more lines with continuation tokens (rare in practice) are not handled here вҖ”\n  // the downstream 2-line and 3-line join candidates cover those cases instead.\n  const mergedLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < capsCoalesced.length; i++) {\n    const line = capsCoalesced[i];\n    if (i + 1 < capsCoalesced.length) {\n      const nextText = capsCoalesced[i + 1].text;\n      if (/^[/&+:(]/.test(nextText)) {\n        mergedLines.push({ text: `${line.text} ${nextText}`, index: line.index });\n        i++;\n        continue;\n      }\n    }\n    mergedLines.push(line);\n  }\n\n  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n  const seen = new Set<string>();\n\n  // Build a set of positions to skip: short ALL_CAPS lines immediately following metadata\n  const metadataContinuationPositions = new Set<number>();\n  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length - 1; i++) {\n    if (looksLikeMetadata(mergedLines[i].text)) {\n      const next = mergedLines[i + 1];\n      if (isAllCaps(next.text) && wordCount(next.text) <= 2 && next.text.length <= 15) {\n        metadataContinuationPositions.add(next.index);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n    const line = mergedLines[i];\n\n    // Skip metadata continuation fragments\n    if (metadataContinuationPositions.has(line.index)) continue;\n\n    // Single line вҖ” strip page-number prefixes and parenthetical glosses before scoring\n    const singleText = stripParentheticalGloss(stripPageNumber(line.text));\n    if (passesHardFilters(singleText)) {\n      const norm = singleText.toLowerCase();\n      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n        seen.add(norm);\n        candidates.push({ text: singleText, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 2-line join вҖ” skip if first line is a section label AND join would be вүӨ2 words\n    // (a section label followed by modifiers is likely a recipe title, not a category header)\n    if (i + 1 < mergedLines.length) {\n      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text}`;\n      const shouldBlock2 = isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n        (wordCount(joined2) <= 2 || isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(line.text));\n      if (!shouldBlock2 && passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 3-line join вҖ” skip if first line is a section label AND join would be вүӨ2 words\n    if (i + 2 < mergedLines.length) {\n      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text} ${mergedLines[i + 2].text}`;\n      const shouldBlock3 = isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n        (wordCount(joined3) <= 2 || isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(line.text));\n      if (!shouldBlock3 && passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      return aShort - bShort;\n    });\n    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n  }\n\n  return candidates;\n}\n\n// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\nlet cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n\nexport function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n}\n\nexport async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n  text: string,\n  embed: EmbedFn\n): Promise<string | undefined> {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n\n  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Cache reference embeddings\n  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n\n  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with вүҘ2 words where every significant word has вүҘ4 alpha letters.\n  // Insignificant tokens (вүӨ1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n  };\n\n  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n  }\n\n  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n\n  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n      if (other === sc) continue;\n      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n      );\n      if (hasTruncation) {\n        sc.rawScore = -1.0;  // Hard disqualification вҖ” truncated OCR artifact\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => {\n        const scoreDiff = a.rawScore - b.rawScore;\n        if (Math.abs(scoreDiff) > 0.03) return scoreDiff > 0 ? a : b;\n        // Tiebreak: single-line origin beats multi-line joins (avoids conflating two separate headings)\n        if (a.origin === \"single\" && b.origin !== \"single\") return a;\n        if (b.origin === \"single\" && a.origin !== \"single\") return b;\n        // Tiebreak: more words (more specific) вҶ’ better\n        const wcDiff = wordCount(b.text) - wordCount(a.text);\n        if (wcDiff !== 0) return wcDiff > 0 ? b : a;\n        // Tiebreak: earlier position вҶ’ better\n        return a.position < b.position ? a : b;\n      })\n    : null;\n  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n\n  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n  let firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n    rawScored.find((c) => {\n      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n    }) ?? baseHeading\n  );\n\n  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker вҖ” amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n      : 1.0;\n\n    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings.\n    // Single-word ALL_CAPS terms are overwhelmingly section/category labels, not recipe titles;\n    // real recipe titles in ALL_CAPS are almost always multi-word. Reduce the bonus for single words.\n    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n      ? (wordCount(rs.text) >= 2 ? 0.08 : 0.03)\n      : 0;\n\n    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n\n    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n    // baseScore excludes position factor вҖ” used for diagnostics and ranking\n    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n  });\n\n  if (scored.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // --- Pre-threshold bilingual title detection ---\n  // When a mixed-case candidate at position 0 is followed by an ALL_CAPS candidate\n  // at position вүӨ 2 that is semantically similar to it, this is a bilingual recipe\n  // page (e.g., Polish title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization). Suppress confirmed\n  // translation candidates before computing threshold so their bonuses don't inflate\n  // the threshold beyond the mixed-case title's reach.\n  // Note: we check position вүӨ 2 (local proximity), not global ALL_CAPS count, so\n  // section headers later in the document (SKЕҒADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc.) are irrelevant.\n  let translationCandidates: typeof scored = [];\n  let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n  const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n  if (prePos0) {\n    const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n      (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2 && s.origin === \"single\"\n    );\n    const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n\n    // Method 1: embedding similarity (works for related languages)\n    if (pos0Embedding && nearbyAllCaps.length > 0) {\n      translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n        const capEmbedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === cap.text)?.embedding;\n        if (!capEmbedding) return false;\n        return cosineSimilarity(pos0Embedding, capEmbedding) > 0.4;\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Method 2: layout-based detection (cross-lingual fallback).\n    // When embedding similarity is insufficient (e.g. Polish вҶ” Korean romanization),\n    // detect bilingual layout by position and word overlap:\n    // mixed-case вүҘ2 words at pos 0 + ALL_CAPS вүҘ2 words at pos 1-2 with no shared words.\n    if (translationCandidates.length === 0 && wordCount(prePos0.text) >= 2) {\n      const pos0Words = new Set(\n        prePos0.text.toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 2)\n      );\n      translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n        if (wordCount(cap.text) < 2) return false;\n        const capWords = cap.text.toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 2);\n        return !capWords.some((w) => pos0Words.has(w));\n      });\n    }\n\n    if (translationCandidates.length > 0) {\n      // Suppress standalone translations and any multi-line joins that embed the translation\n      // as a suffix or substring (e.g. \"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" ends with\n      // the translation; \"Title GREEN BEANS BORKEUM к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ\" includes it as a substring).\n      scoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n        const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n        return !translationCandidates.some((t) => {\n          const tLower = t.text.toLowerCase();\n          return sLower.startsWith(tLower) ||\n                 sLower.endsWith(\" \" + tLower) ||\n                 sLower.includes(\" \" + tLower);\n        });\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Fix 2: If the structural heading was identified as a bilingual translation, reassign it.\n  // This prevents the translation's ALL_CAPS bonus from inflating the threshold and ensures\n  // the fallback path in scored also uses the correct heading.\n  if (\n    translationCandidates.length > 0 &&\n    firstStructuralHeading &&\n    translationCandidates.some((t) => t.text === firstStructuralHeading!.text)\n  ) {\n    const nonTranslationStructural = structuralCandidates.filter(\n      (sc) => !translationCandidates.some((t) => t.text === sc.text)\n    );\n    const newHeading = nonTranslationStructural.length > 0\n      ? nonTranslationStructural.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n      : undefined;\n\n    // Patch scored array: remove old structural bonus, apply new one\n    for (const s of scored) {\n      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) {\n        s.score -= 0.10;\n        s.baseScore -= 0.10;\n      }\n      if (newHeading && s.text === newHeading.text) {\n        s.score += 0.10;\n        s.baseScore += 0.10;\n      }\n    }\n    // Update reference for downstream prefix-removal logic\n    firstStructuralHeading = newHeading ?? undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n\n  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  let selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n\n  // Empty-pool fallback: when threshold filtering discards every candidate,\n  // the hard filters' structural verdict should not be overruled by weak\n  // embedding differentiation. Return the best positional candidate.\n  if (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n    const fallback = scored\n      .slice()\n      .sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n    selected = [fallback[0]];\n  }\n\n  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n  // the threshold. Cases:\n  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join (2-line or 3-line) survived the threshold\n  // and its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix/suffix\n  // so the dedup \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n  // Note: the pre-merge step above already handles the common Baked Eggs case (&/continuation\n  // on next line) by turning it into a single candidate вҖ” this block covers the rarer case where\n  // a continuation-character join was generated as a 2-line/3-line candidate and the prefix\n  // single also survived threshold independently (e.g. from a different code path or OCR layout).\n  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( вҖ” digit continuations\n  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mД…ki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Remove PREFIX singles whose continuation join also survived\n      const isPrefixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n      });\n      if (isPrefixOfJoin) return false;\n      // Remove SUFFIX singles (e.g. \"& Coriander\") whose parent join also survived\n      const isSuffixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!jLower.endsWith(\" \" + sLower)) return false;\n        // Only remove if the suffix starts with a continuation character\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(sLower);\n      });\n      if (isSuffixOfJoin) return false;\n      return true;\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Pre-dedup: remove sub-section headers that are substrings of other surviving candidates.\n  // A sub-section header is an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by ingredient-like lines in the source.\n  // Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (bread section header, followed by \"500 g mД…ki\") is a substring of\n  // \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (the real title). Without this filter, dedup kills the title.\n  selected = selected.filter((candidate) => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(candidate.text)) return true;\n    // Check if this candidate is immediately followed by ingredient-like content\n    const nextSourceLines = lines.slice(candidate.position + 1, candidate.position + 2);\n    const followedByIngredients = nextSourceLines.some(\n      (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || startsWithNumber(l.trim())\n    );\n    if (!followedByIngredients) return true;\n    // Only remove if a longer candidate contains this one as a substring\n    const candidateLower = candidate.text.toLowerCase();\n    const hasLongerParent = rawScored.some(\n      (other) =>\n        other.text !== candidate.text &&\n        other.text.length > candidate.text.length &&\n        other.text.toLowerCase().includes(candidateLower)\n    );\n    return !hasLongerParent;\n  });\n\n  // Protect multi-line joins from being destroyed by their own component singles.\n  // When \"Lamb Stew\" (2-line join) survives AND both \"Lamb\" and \"Stew\" (singles) also survive,\n  // the join is the intended title вҖ” remove the singles.\n  const joinsToProtect = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  if (joinsToProtect.length > 0) {\n    const singlesToRemove = new Set<string>();\n    for (const join of joinsToProtect) {\n      const joinWords = join.text.split(/\\s+/);\n      const componentSingles = selected.filter(\n        (s) => s.origin === \"single\" && joinWords.some((w) => s.text.toLowerCase() === w.toLowerCase())\n      );\n      if (componentSingles.length >= Math.min(joinWords.length, 2)) {\n        componentSingles.forEach((s) => singlesToRemove.add(s.text));\n      }\n    }\n    if (singlesToRemove.size > 0) {\n      selected = selected.filter((s) => s.origin !== \"single\" || !singlesToRemove.has(s.text));\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Protect position-0 compound titles from distant sub-section headers.\n  // When a position-0 compound title is longer and contains a shorter candidate\n  // that appears > 10 lines later, remove the distant candidate so the dedup\n  // (shorter-wins rule) doesn't destroy the compound title.\n  const pos0Compounds = selected.filter((s) => s.position === 0);\n  if (pos0Compounds.length > 0) {\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.position === 0) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      return !pos0Compounds.some(\n        (p0) =>\n          p0.position + 10 < s.position &&\n          s.text.length < p0.text.length &&\n          p0.text.toLowerCase().includes(sLower)\n      );\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC вҖ” it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mД…ki 3 ziemniaki\".\n  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (вүҘ2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page вҖ”\n  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors вҶ’ mixed-case multi-title page вҶ’ keep all.\n  if (selected.length > 1) {\n    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n      // Check whether non-first ALL_CAPS headings are section headers within one recipe\n      // (followed immediately by ingredient-like content) rather than separate recipe titles.\n      // A multi-recipe page has body text between titles; a single-recipe page has\n      // ingredient lines immediately after each section heading.\n      const sortedCaps = [...allCapsSelected].sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n      const isSubHeader = sortedCaps.slice(1).every((cap) => {\n        const nextLines = lines.slice(cap.position + 1, cap.position + 3);\n        return nextLines.some(\n          (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || /^\\s*\\d/.test(l.trim())\n        );\n      });\n      if (isSubHeader) {\n        selected = [sortedCaps[0]];\n      } else {\n        selected = allCapsSelected;\n      }\n    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n      const theCapCandidate = allCapsSelected[0];\n      // Use non-empty line count so the 75% threshold is consistent regardless of blank-line density.\n      const nonEmptyCount = lines.filter((l) => l.trim().length > 0).length;\n      const capRelPos = theCapCandidate.position / Math.max(nonEmptyCount, 1);\n      // If the sole ALL_CAPS candidate is in the last 25% of the document,\n      // it's likely a category footer, not a title. Prefer the best earlier candidate.\n      if (capRelPos > 0.75) {\n        const earlierCandidates = selected.filter(\n          (s) => s.position / Math.max(nonEmptyCount, 1) <= 0.75\n        );\n        if (earlierCandidates.length > 0) {\n          selected = [earlierCandidates.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n        } else {\n          // All candidates are in the last 25% вҖ” no positional basis to prefer one over another;\n          // fall back to score, accepting that the guard cannot help here.\n          selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n        }\n      } else {\n        selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n\n  if (selected.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n}\n\n/**\n * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n */\nexport function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n    return line;\n  }\n\n  return undefined;\n}\n","numLines":933,"startLine":1,"totalLines":933}}}
