{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BjTm9ey43SxbPQR9KgCxos","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Iteration 17 вҶ’ 18 Improvement Plan\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’## Failure summary\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’| File | Expected | Got | Root cause |\n     6вҶ’|------|----------|-----|------------|\n     7вҶ’| Faszerowana papryka.real.txt | Faszerowana papryka | WARZYWA | ALL_CAPS category footer bypasses filters, wins on bonus |\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’---\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’## Root cause analysis\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’### RC-1: `SECTION_LABELS` missing Polish food-category chapter headers\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’\"WARZYWA\" (vegetables) is a chapter/category divider in a recipe book вҖ” structurally identical to \"SKЕҒADNIKI\" (ingredients) or \"PRZYGOTOWANIE\" (preparation), but from a different vocabulary. The current `SECTION_LABELS` set covers *recipe-internal* section labels (ingredients, instructions, tips) but not *book-level* category labels (vegetables, meats, soups, desserts).\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’These category labels appear as ALL_CAPS single words at page boundaries (typically last or first line). They are never recipe titles.\n    18вҶ’\n    19вҶ’### RC-2: Multi-title guard collapses to highest score without positional awareness\n    20вҶ’\n    21вҶ’When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives alongside mixed-case candidates, the guard picks the highest scorer unconditionally (line 738):\n    22вҶ’\n    23вҶ’```typescript\n    24вҶ’} else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n    25вҶ’  selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n    26вҶ’}\n    27вҶ’```\n    28вҶ’\n    29вҶ’This conflates two situations:\n    30вҶ’- ALL_CAPS is the real title вҶ’ collapse is correct\n    31вҶ’- ALL_CAPS is a footer/category label that scored marginally higher due to bonus вҶ’ collapse is wrong\n    32вҶ’\n    33вҶ’The guard has no concept of document structure: a label on the last line of the document (after all recipe content) should not beat a title on line 0.\n    34вҶ’\n    35вҶ’### RC-3: `allCapsBonus` applies unconditionally to single-word ALL_CAPS\n    36вҶ’\n    37вҶ’The +0.08 `allCapsBonus` fires for any ALL_CAPS text with вүҘ4 alpha characters (line 499). Single-word ALL_CAPS terms like `WARZYWA` receive the full bonus despite being ineligible for the `isStructuralHeading` slot (which requires вүҘ2 words). This amplifies weak category-label candidates enough to overtake legitimate titles.\n    38вҶ’\n    39вҶ’### Common theme\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’All three root causes share one failure mode: **the ALL_CAPS preference system elevates vocabulary-category labels that are structurally indistinguishable from titles under current filters**. The actual title вҖ” on line 0 with strong positional signal вҖ” loses because the algorithm's ALL_CAPS bias is unguarded against labels appearing after body content.\n    42вҶ’\n    43вҶ’---\n    44вҶ’\n    45вҶ’## Proposed changes\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’### Change 1: Expand `SECTION_LABELS` with Polish food-category labels\n    48вҶ’\n    49вҶ’**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` вҖ” `SECTION_LABELS` set\n    50вҶ’\n    51вҶ’**What:** Add common Polish recipe-book chapter/category headers (stored without diacritics, matching existing convention).\n    52вҶ’\n    53вҶ’**Before:**\n    54вҶ’```typescript\n    55вҶ’const SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n    56вҶ’  // English\n    57вҶ’  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n    58вҶ’  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n    59вҶ’  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n    60вҶ’  // Polish (stored without diacritics for OCR resilience)\n    61вҶ’  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n    62вҶ’  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n    63вҶ’  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n    64вҶ’]);\n    65вҶ’```\n    66вҶ’\n    67вҶ’**After:**\n    68вҶ’```typescript\n    69вҶ’const SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n    70вҶ’  // English\n    71вҶ’  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n    72вҶ’  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n    73вҶ’  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n    74вҶ’  // Polish вҖ” recipe section labels (stored without diacritics for OCR resilience)\n    75вҶ’  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n    76вҶ’  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n    77вҶ’  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n    78вҶ’  // Polish вҖ” recipe-book chapter/category labels (food groups, meal types)\n    79вҶ’  \"warzywa\",          // vegetables\n    80вҶ’  \"mieso\",            // meat (miДҷso)\n    81вҶ’  \"miesa\",            // meats (miДҷsa)\n    82вҶ’  \"ryby\",             // fish\n    83вҶ’  \"owoce morza\",      // seafood\n    84вҶ’  \"zupy\",             // soups\n    85вҶ’  \"salatki\",          // salads (saЕӮatki)\n    86вҶ’  \"desery\",           // desserts\n    87вҶ’  \"napoje\",           // drinks\n    88вҶ’  \"pieczywo\",         // bread/baked goods\n    89вҶ’  \"przekaski\",        // appetizers/snacks\n    90вҶ’  \"sniadania\",        // breakfasts (Еӣniadania)\n    91вҶ’  \"obiady\",           // dinners/lunches\n    92вҶ’  \"kolacje\",          // suppers\n    93вҶ’  \"makarony\",         // pasta dishes\n    94вҶ’  \"kasza\",            // groats/grains\n    95вҶ’  \"kasze\",            // groats/grains (plural)\n    96вҶ’  \"dania glowne\",     // main courses (dania gЕӮГіwne)\n    97вҶ’  \"przystawki\",       // starters\n    98вҶ’  \"dodatki\",          // side dishes\n    99вҶ’  \"przetwory\",        // preserves\n   100вҶ’  \"wypieki\",          // baked goods\n   101вҶ’  \"ciasta\",           // cakes (plural)\n   102вҶ’  \"ciastka\",          // cookies\n   103вҶ’  \"torty\",            // layer cakes\n   104вҶ’  \"placki\",           // pancakes/flatbreads\n   105вҶ’  \"koktajle\",         // cocktails/smoothies\n   106вҶ’]);\n   107вҶ’```\n   108вҶ’\n   109вҶ’**Why this works:** Directly catches `WARZYWA` (normalized to `warzywa`) at the hard-filter stage. It never becomes a candidate, so the downstream scoring and guard logic never sees it.\n   110вҶ’\n   111вҶ’**Risk:** Extremely low. These are generic food-category words, not dish names. No legitimate recipe title is just \"WARZYWA\" or \"ZUPY\".\n   112вҶ’\n   113вҶ’### Change 2: Position-aware single-ALL_CAPS guard\n   114вҶ’\n   115вҶ’**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` вҖ” multi-title guard block (~line 737)\n   116вҶ’\n   117вҶ’**What:** When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives alongside mixed-case candidates, check whether the ALL_CAPS candidate appears in the last 25% of the document. If so, prefer the highest-scoring candidate from the first half of the document instead. This catches category footers that slip past `SECTION_LABELS`.\n   118вҶ’\n   119вҶ’**Before:**\n   120вҶ’```typescript\n   121вҶ’} else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   122вҶ’  selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   123вҶ’}\n   124вҶ’```\n   125вҶ’\n   126вҶ’**After:**\n   127вҶ’```typescript\n   128вҶ’} else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   129вҶ’  const theCapCandidate = allCapsSelected[0];\n   130вҶ’  const capRelPos = theCapCandidate.position / lines.length;\n   131вҶ’  // If the sole ALL_CAPS candidate is in the last 25% of the document,\n   132вҶ’  // it's likely a category footer, not a title. Prefer the best earlier candidate.\n   133вҶ’  if (capRelPos > 0.75) {\n   134вҶ’    const earlierCandidates = selected.filter(\n   135вҶ’      (s) => s.position / lines.length <= 0.75\n   136вҶ’    );\n   137вҶ’    if (earlierCandidates.length > 0) {\n   138вҶ’      selected = [earlierCandidates.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   139вҶ’    } else {\n   140вҶ’      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   141вҶ’    }\n   142вҶ’  } else {\n   143вҶ’    selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   144вҶ’  }\n   145вҶ’}\n   146вҶ’```\n   147вҶ’\n   148вҶ’**Why this works:** Recipe titles appear at or near the top of the page. A single ALL_CAPS word at the very end of a recipe page (after ingredients and instructions) is almost always a section/category marker for the next chapter. This heuristic provides a structural safety net for category labels not in `SECTION_LABELS`.\n   149вҶ’\n   150вҶ’**Risk:** Low. Legitimate ALL_CAPS titles at position >75% are rare вҖ” recipe titles appear at the top, not the bottom. Even if such a case exists, the candidate would need to be the *sole* ALL_CAPS survivor AND be competing with mixed-case candidates to trigger this path.\n   151вҶ’\n   152вҶ’### Change 3: Reduce `allCapsBonus` for single-word candidates\n   153вҶ’\n   154вҶ’**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` вҖ” allCapsBonus computation (~line 499)\n   155вҶ’\n   156вҶ’**What:** Reduce the ALL_CAPS bonus from +0.08 to +0.03 for single-word candidates. Multi-word ALL_CAPS candidates keep the full +0.08.\n   157вҶ’\n   158вҶ’**Before:**\n   159вҶ’```typescript\n   160вҶ’const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   161вҶ’  ? 0.08\n   162вҶ’  : 0;\n   163вҶ’```\n   164вҶ’\n   165вҶ’**After:**\n   166вҶ’```typescript\n   167вҶ’const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   168вҶ’  ? (wordCount(rs.text) >= 2 ? 0.08 : 0.03)\n   169вҶ’  : 0;\n   170вҶ’```\n   171вҶ’\n   172вҶ’**Why this works:** Single-word ALL_CAPS terms are overwhelmingly section/category labels, not recipe titles. Real recipe titles in ALL_CAPS are almost always multi-word (\"KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA\", \"LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS\"). Reducing the bonus for single words narrows the score gap between `WARZYWA` (+0.03) and `Faszerowana papryka` (no bonus but position factor ~1.12Г—), making the position factor decisive.\n   173вҶ’\n   174вҶ’**Risk:** Low-moderate. If a legitimate single-word ALL_CAPS recipe title exists (e.g., \"TZATZIKI\"), it would still get +0.03 bonus plus potential structural heading bonus if applicable. The reduction from 0.08 to 0.03 is small enough that a genuinely title-like embedding score would still win.\n   175вҶ’\n   176вҶ’---\n   177вҶ’\n   178вҶ’## Defense-in-depth analysis\n   179вҶ’\n   180вҶ’These three changes form concentric defensive layers:\n   181вҶ’\n   182вҶ’| Layer | What it catches | When it fires |\n   183вҶ’|-------|----------------|---------------|\n   184вҶ’| **Change 1** (SECTION_LABELS) | Known Polish category labels | Hard filter вҖ” before scoring |\n   185вҶ’| **Change 3** (reduced bonus) | Unknown single-word ALL_CAPS labels | Scoring вҖ” reduces their competitive edge |\n   186вҶ’| **Change 2** (position guard) | Any ALL_CAPS footer that slips through | Multi-title guard вҖ” last-resort structural check |\n   187вҶ’\n   188вҶ’For the `WARZYWA` case, Change 1 alone is sufficient. Changes 2 and 3 provide safety against future category labels not in the set (e.g., regional or specialized recipe-book sections).\n   189вҶ’\n   190вҶ’---\n   191вҶ’\n   192вҶ’## Expected impact\n   193вҶ’\n   194вҶ’| Metric | Before | After |\n   195вҶ’|--------|--------|-------|\n   196вҶ’| Faszerowana papryka | FAIL (`WARZYWA`) | PASS (`Faszerowana papryka`) |\n   197вҶ’| All other 10 recipes | PASS | PASS (no regression expected) |\n   198вҶ’| **Accuracy** | **90.9% (10/11)** | **100% (11/11)** |\n   199вҶ’\n   200вҶ’### Regression risk assessment\n   201вҶ’\n   202вҶ’- **KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA** (multi-word ALL_CAPS title): Unaffected вҖ” multi-word candidates keep full +0.08 bonus; position is early in document.\n   203вҶ’- **LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS** (multi-word ALL_CAPS title): Unaffected вҖ” same reasons.\n   204вҶ’- **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** (contains \"WARZYWAMI\"): Unaffected вҖ” \"WARZYWAMI\" вү  \"WARZYWA\" and appears as part of multi-word title, not standalone.\n   205вҶ’- **Bilingual recipes** (SmaЕјona zielona fasolka): Unaffected вҖ” translation detection runs independently of these changes.\n   206вҶ’\n   207вҶ’### What could still fail in the future\n   208вҶ’\n   209вҶ’- **Uncommon Polish category labels** not in the expanded set (e.g., \"GRZYBY\" = mushrooms, \"JAJKA\" = eggs). Mitigation: Change 2 (position guard) catches these structurally.\n   210вҶ’- **Recipe titles that are also food categories** (e.g., a recipe simply called \"Zupy\" for a specific soup). Mitigation: extremely unlikely вҖ” recipe titles are specific dish names, not generic food categories. If it does happen, the title would need to be ALL_CAPS + single word + in the last 25% of the page to be incorrectly filtered, which is an unlikely combination.\n   211вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014867ti9qiG3i71fZNmJ1wr","session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"bf2ee616-09d5-4aa7-9f9d-69b7f8e898e5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T5pzSYeM95Ca8ZQK79gNeU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Iteration 16 Failure Analysis\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’## Failing Case\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’**File:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka.real.txt`\n     6вҶ’**Expected:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`\n     7вҶ’**Got:** `''` (undefined / empty)\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’---\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’## Input Structure\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’```\n    14вҶ’Line 0: SmaЕјona zielona fasolka        вҶҗ Polish title (mixed-case)\n    15вҶ’Line 1: GREEN BEANS BORKEUM            вҶҗ English translation (ALL_CAPS)\n    16вҶ’Line 2: к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ лі¶мқҢ                    вҶҗ Korean translation\n    17вҶ’Line 3: Wymyslitem ten pireepis...     вҶҗ Author note (long, garbled)\n    18вҶ’...\n    19вҶ’Line 5: DLA & OSOB                     вҶҗ Serving size (correctly filtered)\n    20вҶ’...\n    21вҶ’Line 9: SKLADNIKI                      вҶҗ Section header (without Д… diacritic)\n    22вҶ’```\n    23вҶ’\n    24вҶ’This is a **trilingual recipe title block**: Polish title immediately followed by ALL_CAPS English romanization and then Korean script.\n    25вҶ’\n    26вҶ’---\n    27вҶ’\n    28вҶ’## Why the Algorithm Fails\n    29вҶ’\n    30вҶ’### 1. Bilingual detection fires on the wrong candidate\n    31вҶ’\n    32вҶ’The bilingual detection logic (`prePos0` + `nearbyAllCaps`) correctly identifies the layout:\n    33вҶ’- `prePos0` = `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` (position 0, mixed-case)\n    34вҶ’- `nearbyAllCaps` = `[\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"]` (position 1, ALL_CAPS, single)\n    35вҶ’- Method 2 (layout-based) confirms translation: no word overlap between Polish and English, both вүҘ 2 words\n    36вҶ’\n    37вҶ’`\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` is removed from `scoredForThreshold`. **This part works correctly.**\n    38вҶ’\n    39вҶ’### 2. Multi-line joins mixing both languages are NOT suppressed\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’The bilingual detection filter removes candidates **starting with** the translation text:\n    42вҶ’\n    43вҶ’```typescript\n    44вҶ’return !translationCandidates.some((t) => sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()));\n    45вҶ’```\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’This does **not** remove:\n    48вҶ’- `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` (2-line join, starts with Polish)\n    49вҶ’- `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ лі¶мқҢ\"` (3-line join, starts with Polish)\n    50вҶ’\n    51вҶ’Both of these pass `passesHardFilters` completely:\n    52вҶ’- Length: 47 and 54 characters respectively (вүӨ 80) вң“\n    53вҶ’- Korean characters are stripped by `/[^a-zA-Z]/g` before garble checks, so they contribute no false-garble signal\n    54вҶ’- Vowel ratio: ~0.46 (Latin letters only) вң“\n    55вҶ’- Multi-word garble check: `\"zielona\"` and `\"fasolka\"` have length 7 > 2, not caught вң“\n    56вҶ’\n    57вҶ’These composite candidates remain in `scoredForThreshold` with composite embeddings that blend Polish food vocabulary and English food terms. Their embedding similarity to the `TITLE_REFERENCE` may be **higher** than the Polish-only title, because `\"GREEN BEANS\"` is strongly associated with recipes in English-language embedding models.\n    58вҶ’\n    59вҶ’### 3. Structural bonus is assigned to the translation, not the title\n    60вҶ’\n    61вҶ’`isStructuralHeading(\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\")` returns `true`:\n    62вҶ’- ALL_CAPS вң“\n    63вҶ’- 3 words вүҘ 2 вң“\n    64вҶ’- All significant words вүҘ 4 uppercase letters: GREEN(5), BEANS(5), BORKEUM(7) вң“\n    65вҶ’\n    66вҶ’`\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` is therefore selected as `firstStructuralHeading` and assigned:\n    67вҶ’- `structuralBonus = 0.10`\n    68вҶ’- `allCapsBonus = 0.08`\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’These bonuses are computed in `scored` **before** bilingual detection. So the real Polish title (`\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"`) receives **no bonuses at all**, while the translation candidate it competes against had already been boosted by 0.18 in the `scored` array used by the fallback path.\n    71вҶ’\n    72вҶ’### 4. Resulting score imbalance causes empty selection or wrong output\n    73вҶ’\n    74вҶ’The combination of factors:\n    75вҶ’\n    76вҶ’1. Polish title has no ALL_CAPS bonus, no structural bonus\n    77вҶ’2. Translation joins (mixing Polish + English) remain in `scoredForThreshold` with inflated composite scores\n    78вҶ’3. If the 2-line or 3-line join has the highest `thresholdScore`, `threshold = 0.7 Г— join_score`, which can exceed the Polish-only title's score\n    79вҶ’4. `selected` after threshold filtering may contain only the contaminated join(s), not the clean single-line title\n    80вҶ’5. The dedup step (`shorter wins`) can only help if the shorter single-line title is **also** in `selected` вҖ” if it didn't pass threshold, it was never added, so dedup never fires\n    81вҶ’\n    82вҶ’This produces either:\n    83вҶ’- `undefined` (if every remaining candidate in `scoredForThreshold` somehow falls below threshold=0.08 and the fallback returns the highest-scored position-0 candidate, which is the join)\n    84вҶ’- Or `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` (the contaminated join, when it's the only survivor above threshold)\n    85вҶ’\n    86вҶ’### 5. `SKLADNIKI` diacritic stripping bypasses section-label filter\n    87вҶ’\n    88вҶ’A secondary (non-blocking) issue: the OCR text contains `\"SKLADNIKI\"` (without the `Д…`). The `SECTION_LABELS` set contains `\"skЕӮadniki\"` (with `Д…`). The `isSectionLabel` normalization does:\n    89вҶ’\n    90вҶ’```typescript\n    91вҶ’text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase()  // вҶ’ \"skladniki\"\n    92вҶ’```\n    93вҶ’\n    94вҶ’This does **not** match `\"skЕӮadniki\"`, so `\"SKLADNIKI\"` enters the candidate pool. Its embedding correctly classifies it as a header (high `headerSim`), so it doesn't win вҖ” but it adds noise to the threshold calculation.\n    95вҶ’\n    96вҶ’---\n    97вҶ’\n    98вҶ’## Common Themes\n    99вҶ’\n   100вҶ’There is only one failure in this iteration. Its root causes map to known algorithm limitations:\n   101вҶ’\n   102вҶ’1. **Bilingual join contamination**: The bilingual filter suppresses standalone translation candidates but not multi-line joins that *start* with the primary title and *include* the translation. The English vocabulary in those joins boosts their embedding score above the clean Polish-only candidate.\n   103вҶ’\n   104вҶ’2. **Structural bonus misallocation**: When the ALL_CAPS line is a translation rather than the recipe title, `isStructuralHeading` still fires on it, assigning the 0.10 structural bonus to the wrong candidate. The `scored` array (used in the empty-pool fallback) retains this inflated score even after bilingual suppression.\n   105вҶ’\n   106вҶ’3. **Diacritic-stripped section labels bypass the filter**: OCR regularly drops Polish diacritics. Section labels stored with diacritics (`skЕӮadniki`, `przygotowanie`) don't match their diacritic-stripped OCR forms (`skladniki`, `przygotowanie` is fine since it has no diacritics, but `skЕӮadniki` вҶ’ `skladniki` fails). This allows section headers into the candidate pool.\n   107вҶ’\n   108вҶ’---\n   109вҶ’\n   110вҶ’## Fix Direction\n   111вҶ’\n   112вҶ’The bilingual filter should also suppress candidates where **any** of the translation candidates appear as a **contiguous suffix** of the candidate text вҖ” not just as a prefix/start. Specifically:\n   113вҶ’\n   114вҶ’```\n   115вҶ’\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"\n   116вҶ’```\n   117вҶ’\n   118вҶ’contains `\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` as a suffix. Extending the suppression to:\n   119вҶ’\n   120вҶ’```typescript\n   121вҶ’return !translationCandidates.some((t) =>\n   122вҶ’  sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()) ||\n   123вҶ’  sLower.endsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()) ||\n   124вҶ’  sLower.includes(\" \" + t.text.toLowerCase())\n   125вҶ’);\n   126вҶ’```\n   127вҶ’\n   128вҶ’вҖҰwould remove all composite joins that embed the translation, leaving `\"SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\"` as the dominant candidate in `scoredForThreshold`.\n   129вҶ’\n   130вҶ’Separately, the structural bonus should not be assigned to a candidate that was subsequently identified as a translation вҖ” the structural heading selection and bilingual detection should run together before bonuses are finalized.\n   131вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014867ti9qiG3i71fZNmJ1wr","session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"fb282758-5d4c-41ad-9491-58b6b4916891"}
