{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017HUWZzYWEX8coW4qckk3nn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Iteration 15 вҖ” Failure Analysis\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’## Failure 1: KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA вҶ’ got `UuIw`\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’**Input structure (first 6 non-empty lines):**\n     6вҶ’```\n     7вҶ’/ Jesien / Zupy         вҶҗ line 0 вҖ” book breadcrumb (Autumn / Soups)\n     8вҶ’KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA вҶҗ line 1 вҖ” the actual title\n     9вҶ’DLA 4 OSГ“B              вҶҗ line 2 вҖ” serving size (filtered correctly)\n    10вҶ’PRZYGOTOWANIE 10 MIN    вҶҗ line 3 вҖ” metadata (filtered correctly)\n    11вҶ’GOTOWANIE 30 MIN        вҶҗ line 4 вҖ” metadata (filtered correctly)\n    12вҶ’UuIw                    вҶҗ line 5 вҖ” garbled OCR\n    13вҶ’```\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’**Why it fails вҖ” two compounding bugs:**\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’**Bug A: Bilingual detection falsely suppresses the title.**\n    18вҶ’\n    19вҶ’`/ Jesien / Zupy` (a category breadcrumb) is at position 0 and is mixed-case, so it becomes `prePos0`. `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` is at position 1, ALL_CAPS, single-origin вҖ” it enters `nearbyAllCaps`.\n    20вҶ’\n    21вҶ’The layout-based bilingual fallback then fires:\n    22вҶ’- `pos0Words = {\"jesien\", \"zupy\"}`\n    23вҶ’- `capWords = {\"krem\", \"selerowy\", \"gorgonzola\"}`\n    24вҶ’- No word overlap вҶ’ classified as a \"translation candidate\"\n    25вҶ’\n    26вҶ’`KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` is suppressed from `scoredForThreshold`. The real title is no longer competing.\n    27вҶ’\n    28вҶ’Root cause: `/ Jesien / Zupy` is a **forward-slash-separated breadcrumb** (chapter/season navigation), not a recipe title in another language. The existing pipe filter (`text.includes(\" | \")`) would have caught it if it used ` | `, but it uses ` / ` instead.\n    29вҶ’\n    30вҶ’**Bug B: `UuIw` passes the garbled-text filter.**\n    31вҶ’\n    32вҶ’`UuIw` is clearly OCR noise, but `isLikelyGarbled` does not flag it:\n    33вҶ’- 4 letters вҖ” the single-word short check requires `letters.length <= 3`; 4 letters escapes it\n    34вҶ’- Mixed case (U-u-I-w) вҖ” not detected by any specific pattern\n    35вҶ’- Vowel ratio: U, u, I = 3/4 = 0.75 вҖ” within the 0.15вҖ“0.85 range\n    36вҶ’\n    37вҶ’So after the real title is suppressed, `UuIw` wins.\n    38вҶ’\n    39вҶ’---\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’## Failure 2: LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS вҶ’ got `BALLS`\n    42вҶ’\n    43вҶ’**Input structure (relevant lines):**\n    44вҶ’```\n    45вҶ’LABANEH          вҶҗ line 0 \\\n    46вҶ’BALLS            вҶҗ line 1  |вҖ” 4-line title, correctly merged\n    47вҶ’WITH NIGELLA     вҶҗ line 2  |\n    48вҶ’SEEDS            вҶҗ line 3 /\n    49вҶ’[long prose Г—9 lines]\n    50вҶ’MAKES 25 LABANEH вҶҗ line 12 вҖ” metadata, filtered by MAKES pattern\n    51вҶ’BALLS            вҶҗ line 13 вҖ” repeat fragment, survives as standalone\n    52вҶ’```\n    53вҶ’\n    54вҶ’**Why it fails:**\n    55вҶ’\n    56вҶ’The `capsCoalesced` logic correctly merges lines 0вҖ“3 into `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` вҖ” this is working as designed.\n    57вҶ’\n    58вҶ’However, line 13 (`BALLS`) is a second occurrence in the source: the tail end of \"MAKES 25 LABANEH BALLS\" after the `MAKES 25 LABANEH` prefix gets filtered as metadata. `BALLS` alone passes all hard filters and enters the candidate pool at position 13.\n    59вҶ’\n    60вҶ’In the dedup step, the \"shorter wins\" rule removes `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` because `BALLS` is a shorter substring of it:\n    61вҶ’\n    62вҶ’```\n    63вҶ’aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) && b.text.length < a.text.length\n    64вҶ’вҶ’ \"labaneh balls with nigella seeds\".includes(\"balls\") && 5 < 32  вҶ’ true\n    65вҶ’```\n    66вҶ’\n    67вҶ’`LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` is eliminated; `BALLS` survives.\n    68вҶ’\n    69вҶ’The pre-dedup sub-section header filter does not help here because `BALLS` (at position 13) is followed by prose (the recipe method), not ingredients, so `followedByIngredients = false` and it is kept.\n    70вҶ’\n    71вҶ’Root cause: A metadata line (`MAKES 25 LABANEH BALLS`) deposits a fragment (`BALLS`) into the candidate pool after its prefix is filtered. This fragment then destructs the correctly assembled title via the \"shorter wins\" dedup rule.\n    72вҶ’\n    73вҶ’---\n    74вҶ’\n    75вҶ’## Failure 3: SmaЕјona zielona fasolka вҶ’ got `DLA & OSOB`\n    76вҶ’\n    77вҶ’**Input structure (first 10 non-empty lines):**\n    78вҶ’```\n    79вҶ’SmaЕјona zielona fasolka  вҶҗ line 0 вҖ” the title (Polish)\n    80вҶ’GREEN BEANS BORKEUM      вҶҗ line 1 вҖ” Korean-romanisation translation\n    81вҶ’к·ёлҰ°л№Ҳ лі¶мқҢ              вҶҗ line 2 вҖ” Korean script (filtered by garble check)\n    82вҶ’[2 lines of Polish prose]\n    83вҶ’DLA & OSOB               вҶҗ line 5 вҖ” OCR-corrupted \"DLA 4 OSГ“B\" (serving size)\n    84вҶ’Przvgetowanie            вҶҗ line 6 вҖ” OCR-corrupted \"Przygotowanie\"\n    85вҶ’15 minut\n    86вҶ’Smazenie 15 minut\n    87вҶ’SKLADNIKI                вҶҗ line 9\n    88вҶ’```\n    89вҶ’\n    90вҶ’**Why it fails:**\n    91вҶ’\n    92вҶ’`DLA & OSOB` is a serving-size notation: Polish `DLA 4 OSГ“B` (\"FOR 4 PEOPLE\"), where OCR misread `4` as `&`.\n    93вҶ’\n    94вҶ’The metadata pattern intended to catch it is `/^DLA\\s+\\d/i`, which requires a **digit** after `DLA`. With `&` in place of `4`, the pattern does not match. `DLA & OSOB` clears all hard filters and is awarded the ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08).\n    95вҶ’\n    96вҶ’The bilingual detection correctly suppresses `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` (as a translation of the Polish title). After that suppression, `scoredForThreshold` contains both `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` and `DLA & OSOB`.\n    97вҶ’\n    98вҶ’The multi-title guard fires (`allCapsSelected.length === 1` = `DLA & OSOB`), collapsing `selected` to the single highest-scoring candidate. `DLA & OSOB`'s ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) combined with its position factor (position 5 in a ~25-line document вҶ’ factor вүҲ 1.07) pushes its final score above `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`, which gets no ALL_CAPS bonus and no structural bonus.\n    99вҶ’\n   100вҶ’Root cause: A single-character OCR substitution (`4` вҶ’ `&`) defeats the serving-size metadata filter. The ALL_CAPS bonus then elevates the corrupted metadata above the actual mixed-case title.\n   101вҶ’\n   102вҶ’---\n   103вҶ’\n   104вҶ’## Common Themes\n   105вҶ’\n   106вҶ’### 1. OCR corruption bypasses hard filters\n   107вҶ’All three failures involve OCR artifacts that slip through. In case 3 a digit becomes `&`, defeating a metadata regex that requires `\\d`. In case 1 `UuIw` has 4 letters instead of вүӨ3, escaping the single-word garble threshold.\n   108вҶ’\n   109вҶ’### 2. Bilingual detection misfires on non-title position-0 lines (case 1)\n   110вҶ’The `prePos0` heuristic assumes any mixed-case line at position 0 is a title. A book breadcrumb like `/ Jesien / Zupy` satisfies this condition and triggers spurious translation-candidate suppression of the real ALL_CAPS title on line 1. The ` / `-separated breadcrumb format is not filtered (only ` | ` is).\n   111вҶ’\n   112вҶ’### 3. Metadata-line fragments pollute the candidate pool (case 2)\n   113вҶ’When a multi-word metadata line (e.g., `MAKES 25 LABANEH BALLS`) is split by the metadata filter, its trailing fragment (`BALLS`) survives independently. The \"shorter wins\" dedup then destroys the correctly merged title that contains the fragment as a substring.\n   114вҶ’\n   115вҶ’### 4. ALL_CAPS bonus can override a correct mixed-case title (case 3)\n   116вҶ’Mixed-case recipe titles (common in books that show the native-language name first) receive no ALL_CAPS bonus. Any ALL_CAPS line that passes hard filters вҖ” even corrupted metadata вҖ” gains 0.08 unconditionally, which can tip the multi-title collapse toward the wrong candidate.\n   117вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014867ti9qiG3i71fZNmJ1wr","session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"1a5ff9a7-0d29-4bd9-97ae-ce6ed245a949"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018c1kKqvEn4DN29LBdzGpwS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Iteration 16 вҖ” Improvement Plan\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’## Overview\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’Three failures, five distinct bugs, but a shared theme: **OCR corruption and edge-case formatting bypass filters designed for clean input**. The fixes below are targeted вҖ” each addresses a specific filter gap rather than restructuring the pipeline. The current architecture (candidate generation вҶ’ embedding scoring вҶ’ dedup) is sound; the failures are at the filter layer.\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’**Accuracy trajectory:** 15 вҶ’ 72.7% (8/11). Three real-input recipes failing. Target: 11/11 (100%).\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’---\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’## Failure 1: KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA вҶ’ `UuIw`\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’**Expected:** `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA`\n    14вҶ’**Got:** `UuIw`\n    15вҶ’\n    16вҶ’### Root Cause Analysis\n    17вҶ’\n    18вҶ’Two compounding bugs:\n    19вҶ’\n    20вҶ’**Bug A: Breadcrumb line triggers false bilingual detection.**\n    21вҶ’\n    22вҶ’`/ Jesien / Zupy` is a book navigation breadcrumb (Autumn / Soups section), not a recipe title. It sits at position 0, is mixed-case, and passes all hard filters. The bilingual layout detection (Method 2, line 517) then fires:\n    23вҶ’\n    24вҶ’- `prePos0 = \"/ Jesien / Zupy\"` (mixed-case at position 0, вүҘ2 words)\n    25вҶ’- `nearbyAllCaps` includes `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` (position 1, ALL_CAPS)\n    26вҶ’- Word sets: `{\"jesien\", \"zupy\"}` vs `{\"krem\", \"selerowy\", \"gorgonzola\"}` вҖ” no overlap\n    27вҶ’- Result: `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` is classified as a \"translation candidate\" and **suppressed**\n    28вҶ’\n    29вҶ’The existing `\" | \"` pipe filter (line 180) was designed for this exact category of separators, but only handles pipe characters. Forward-slash breadcrumbs like `/ Jesien / Zupy` use the same pattern but escape the filter.\n    30вҶ’\n    31вҶ’**Bug B: `UuIw` escapes the garbled-text filter.**\n    32вҶ’\n    33вҶ’After the real title is suppressed, `UuIw` wins by default. It passes `isLikelyGarbled` because:\n    34вҶ’- 4 letters вҖ” the single-word check requires `letters.length <= 3`; 4 escapes it\n    35вҶ’- Vowel ratio 3/4 = 0.75 вҖ” within the 0.15вҖ“0.85 range\n    36вҶ’- No `[a-z][A-Z]` detection exists for mid-word casing transitions\n    37вҶ’\n    38вҶ’### Fix A: Breadcrumb filter in `passesHardFilters`\n    39вҶ’\n    40вҶ’Add a hard filter for lines containing 2+ forward-slash characters. These are navigation breadcrumbs (e.g., `/ Section / Subsection`), never recipe titles.\n    41вҶ’\n    42вҶ’**Before (line 180):**\n    43вҶ’```typescript\n    44вҶ’// Pipe-separated lines are book category/chapter headers, not recipe titles\n    45вҶ’if (text.includes(\" | \")) return false;\n    46вҶ’```\n    47вҶ’\n    48вҶ’**After:**\n    49вҶ’```typescript\n    50вҶ’// Pipe-separated lines are book category/chapter headers, not recipe titles\n    51вҶ’if (text.includes(\" | \")) return false;\n    52вҶ’// Slash-separated breadcrumbs (e.g., \"/ Jesien / Zupy\") are navigation, not titles\n    53вҶ’// Only filter when 2+ slashes are present вҖ” single-slash lines like\n    54вҶ’// \"TITLE / SUBTITLE\" are legitimate continuation-merged titles\n    55вҶ’if ((text.match(/\\//g) || []).length >= 2) return false;\n    56вҶ’```\n    57вҶ’\n    58вҶ’**Safety analysis:**\n    59вҶ’- `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` вҖ” 1 slash. Not filtered. Safe.\n    60вҶ’- `TITLE FIRST PART / SECOND PART` вҖ” 1 slash. Not filtered. Safe.\n    61вҶ’- `/ Jesien / Zupy` вҖ” 2 slashes. Filtered. Correct.\n    62вҶ’- Could any legitimate title have 2+ slashes? Recipe titles don't use `/` as enumeration separators (they use \"and\", \"or\", or \",\"): vanishingly unlikely.\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’### Fix B: Mid-word casing transition in `isLikelyGarbled`\n    65вҶ’\n    66вҶ’Add detection for single words with internal lowercase-to-uppercase transitions. In natural language (English, Polish, Korean romanization), a lowercase letter is never followed by an uppercase letter within a single word. This pattern is diagnostic of OCR noise.\n    67вҶ’\n    68вҶ’**Before (after the single-word short check, around line 137):**\n    69вҶ’```typescript\n    70вҶ’if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    71вҶ’  return true;\n    72вҶ’}\n    73вҶ’```\n    74вҶ’\n    75вҶ’**After (add a new check after the existing single-word check):**\n    76вҶ’```typescript\n    77вҶ’if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    78вҶ’  return true;\n    79вҶ’}\n    80вҶ’\n    81вҶ’// Single word with internal lowercaseвҶ’uppercase transition вҖ” OCR noise (e.g., \"UuIw\", \"aBC\")\n    82вҶ’// No natural language produces this pattern in a single word.\n    83вҶ’if (words.length === 1 && /[a-z][A-Z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n    84вҶ’  return true;\n    85вҶ’}\n    86вҶ’```\n    87вҶ’\n    88вҶ’**Safety analysis:**\n    89вҶ’- `UuIw` вҶ’ `u` followed by `I` вҶ’ filtered. Correct.\n    90вҶ’- `KREM` вҶ’ all uppercase, no `[a-z][A-Z]` match. Safe.\n    91вҶ’- `SmaЕјona` вҶ’ `Еј` (non-ASCII) followed by `o` (lowercase) вҶ’ no match. Safe.\n    92вҶ’- `McRib` вҶ’ hypothetical concern, but no recipe title uses CamelCase brand names as standalone candidates. And this only fires on `words.length === 1`.\n    93вҶ’- All existing test titles: standard Title Case, ALL_CAPS, or sentence case. No `[a-z][A-Z]` transitions. Safe.\n    94вҶ’\n    95вҶ’**Combined effect on Failure 1:**\n    96вҶ’- Fix A prevents `/ Jesien / Zupy` from entering the candidate pool entirely вҶ’ bilingual detection never fires on it вҶ’ `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` is not suppressed вҶ’ it wins as the structural heading.\n    97вҶ’- Fix B provides defense in depth: even if a different code path somehow let `UuIw` compete, it would be filtered as garbled.\n    98вҶ’- Both fixes are independently sufficient to prevent `UuIw` from winning; together they eliminate both root causes.\n    99вҶ’\n   100вҶ’---\n   101вҶ’\n   102вҶ’## Failure 2: LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS вҶ’ `BALLS`\n   103вҶ’\n   104вҶ’**Expected:** `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS`\n   105вҶ’**Got:** `BALLS`\n   106вҶ’\n   107вҶ’### Root Cause Analysis\n   108вҶ’\n   109вҶ’The `capsCoalesced` merge pass (added in iteration 14) correctly assembles lines 0вҖ“3 into `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` at position 0. This is working as designed.\n   110вҶ’\n   111вҶ’The failure is caused by a **metadata fragment leak**. The source text contains:\n   112вҶ’```\n   113вҶ’Line 13: MAKES 25 LABANEH    вҶҗ filtered by /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i\n   114вҶ’Line 14: BALLS               вҶҗ orphaned вҖ” passes all hard filters\n   115вҶ’```\n   116вҶ’\n   117вҶ’These two source lines form a single metadata phrase: \"MAKES 25 LABANEH BALLS\" (yield information). The metadata filter correctly catches line 13, but `BALLS` on line 14 survives as a standalone candidate at position ~14.\n   118вҶ’\n   119вҶ’In the dedup step, `BALLS` eliminates `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` via \"shorter wins\":\n   120вҶ’```\n   121вҶ’\"labaneh balls with nigella seeds\".includes(\"balls\") && 5 < 32 вҶ’ true\n   122вҶ’```\n   123вҶ’\n   124вҶ’The pre-dedup sub-section header filter (line 611) does not help because `BALLS` (position 14) is followed by prose text, so `followedByIngredients = false` and it is kept.\n   125вҶ’\n   126вҶ’### Fix: Metadata continuation suppression\n   127вҶ’\n   128вҶ’When a line is identified as metadata by `looksLikeMetadata`, also suppress the immediately following line if it is a short ALL_CAPS fragment (вүӨ2 words, вүӨ15 chars). This catches the common OCR pattern where yield/serving metadata wraps across two lines.\n   129вҶ’\n   130вҶ’**Implementation location:** In `buildCandidates`, in the candidate generation loop (starting at line 294). Track when the preceding line was metadata and skip the continuation.\n   131вҶ’\n   132вҶ’**Before (line 294):**\n   133вҶ’```typescript\n   134вҶ’for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n   135вҶ’  const line = mergedLines[i];\n   136вҶ’\n   137вҶ’  // Single line\n   138вҶ’  if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n   139вҶ’```\n   140вҶ’\n   141вҶ’**After:**\n   142вҶ’```typescript\n   143вҶ’// Build a set of positions to skip: short ALL_CAPS lines immediately following metadata\n   144вҶ’const metadataContinuationPositions = new Set<number>();\n   145вҶ’for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length - 1; i++) {\n   146вҶ’  if (looksLikeMetadata(mergedLines[i].text)) {\n   147вҶ’    const next = mergedLines[i + 1];\n   148вҶ’    if (isAllCaps(next.text) && wordCount(next.text) <= 2 && next.text.length <= 15) {\n   149вҶ’      metadataContinuationPositions.add(next.index);\n   150вҶ’    }\n   151вҶ’  }\n   152вҶ’}\n   153вҶ’\n   154вҶ’for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n   155вҶ’  const line = mergedLines[i];\n   156вҶ’\n   157вҶ’  // Skip metadata continuation fragments\n   158вҶ’  if (metadataContinuationPositions.has(line.index)) continue;\n   159вҶ’\n   160вҶ’  // Single line\n   161вҶ’  if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n   162вҶ’```\n   163вҶ’\n   164вҶ’**Why this works:**\n   165вҶ’- `MAKES 25 LABANEH` вҶ’ `looksLikeMetadata` returns true\n   166вҶ’- Next line `BALLS` вҶ’ `isAllCaps` true, 1 word, 5 chars вүӨ 15\n   167вҶ’- `BALLS` position is added to `metadataContinuationPositions`\n   168вҶ’- `BALLS` is skipped during candidate generation\n   169вҶ’- `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` (from capsCoalesced at position 0) has no shorter substring competitor in dedup вҶ’ survives intact\n   170вҶ’\n   171вҶ’**Safety analysis:**\n   172вҶ’- Only fires when the **immediately preceding** mergedLine is metadata. Random ALL_CAPS words elsewhere are not affected.\n   173вҶ’- The вүӨ2 words, вүӨ15 chars thresholds ensure only short fragments are suppressed. A legitimate recipe title like `WARZYWA I BOCZEK` (3 words, 16 chars) would not be suppressed even if it followed metadata.\n   174вҶ’- The dedup logic is NOT modified (respecting the \"DO NOT CHANGE\" comment on line 631).\n   175вҶ’- This does not affect any existing test cases: none have a metadata line immediately followed by a short ALL_CAPS word.\n   176вҶ’\n   177вҶ’**Alternative considered вҖ” modifying dedup:** Adding a \"don't let single words eliminate multi-word candidates\" rule to dedup would also fix this case, but it violates the DO NOT CHANGE directive and risks unintended interactions with the carefully tuned dedup/prefix-removal balance.\n   178вҶ’\n   179вҶ’---\n   180вҶ’\n   181вҶ’## Failure 3: SmaЕјona zielona fasolka вҶ’ `DLA & OSOB`\n   182вҶ’\n   183вҶ’**Expected:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`\n   184вҶ’**Got:** `DLA & OSOB`\n   185вҶ’\n   186вҶ’### Root Cause Analysis\n   187вҶ’\n   188вҶ’`DLA & OSOB` is OCR-corrupted Polish serving notation: `DLA 4 OSГ“B` (\"FOR 4 PEOPLE\"), where OCR read `4` as `&` and `Г“` as `O`.\n   189вҶ’\n   190вҶ’The metadata pattern `/^DLA\\s+\\d/i` (line 59) requires a digit after `DLA`. With `&` in place of `4`, the pattern does not match. `DLA & OSOB` then:\n   191вҶ’1. Passes all hard filters\n   192вҶ’2. Receives the ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08)\n   193вҶ’3. In the multi-title guard (line 669), triggers `allCapsSelected.length === 1` вҶ’ collapses to highest-scoring вҶ’ `DLA & OSOB` beats `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` due to the ALL_CAPS bonus and position factor\n   194вҶ’\n   195вҶ’The bilingual detection correctly suppresses `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` вҖ” that part works. The failure is purely that `DLA & OSOB` isn't recognized as metadata.\n   196вҶ’\n   197вҶ’### Fix: OCR-resilient serving-size metadata pattern\n   198вҶ’\n   199вҶ’Replace the narrow digit-dependent pattern with one that recognizes the full structure of Polish serving-size notation: `DLA` + any short token (OCR-corrupted count) + a serving-unit word like `OSOB`/`OSГ“B`/`PORCJI`.\n   200вҶ’\n   201вҶ’Also add a broader pattern that catches `DLA` followed by any single non-word character (common OCR substitution for digits).\n   202вҶ’\n   203вҶ’**Before (line 59):**\n   204вҶ’```typescript\n   205вҶ’/^DLA\\s+\\d/i,\n   206вҶ’```\n   207вҶ’\n   208вҶ’**After:**\n   209вҶ’```typescript\n   210вҶ’/^DLA\\s+\\d/i,\n   211вҶ’// OCR-resilient: \"DLA\" + any token + serving-unit word (handles DLA & OSOB, DLA В§ OSOB, etc.)\n   212вҶ’/^DLA\\s+\\S+\\s+OSOB/i,\n   213вҶ’// OCR-resilient: \"DLA\" + single non-alphanumeric char (common digitвҶ’symbol OCR error)\n   214вҶ’/^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i,\n   215вҶ’```\n   216вҶ’\n   217вҶ’**Why this works:**\n   218вҶ’- `DLA & OSOB` вҶ’ matches `/^DLA\\s+\\S+\\s+OSOB/i` (the `\\S+` swallows `&`, then `OSOB` matches)\n   219вҶ’- `DLA 4 OSГ“B` вҶ’ still matches the original `/^DLA\\s+\\d/i` pattern\n   220вҶ’- `DLA В§ OSOB` вҶ’ matches `/^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i` (hypothetical OCR corruption)\n   221вҶ’- `DLA 6 OSOB` вҶ’ matches original pattern\n   222вҶ’\n   223вҶ’**Safety analysis:**\n   224вҶ’- Could a legitimate recipe title start with `DLA`? In Polish, `DLA` means \"for\" вҖ” theoretically possible (e.g., `DLA PIOTRKA` = \"for Piotr\"), but:\n   225вҶ’  - `/^DLA\\s+\\S+\\s+OSOB/i` requires the third word to be `OSOB*` вҖ” no recipe name contains this\n   226вҶ’  - `/^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i` requires a non-alphanumeric second token вҖ” no recipe name has this\n   227вҶ’- Neither pattern is over-broad. They target specific OCR corruption of a specific metadata format.\n   228вҶ’\n   229вҶ’---\n   230вҶ’\n   231вҶ’## Summary of Changes\n   232вҶ’\n   233вҶ’| # | Change | Location | Lines added | Risk | Fixes |\n   234вҶ’|---|--------|----------|-------------|------|-------|\n   235вҶ’| 1 | Breadcrumb filter (2+ slashes) | `passesHardFilters` | ~2 | Very low | Failure 1 Bug A |\n   236вҶ’| 2 | Mid-word casing garble check | `isLikelyGarbled` | ~4 | Very low | Failure 1 Bug B |\n   237вҶ’| 3 | Metadata continuation suppression | `buildCandidates` | ~10 | Low | Failure 2 |\n   238вҶ’| 4 | OCR-resilient DLA metadata pattern | `METADATA_PATTERNS` | ~2 | Very low | Failure 3 |\n   239вҶ’\n   240вҶ’**Total: ~18 lines of new code across 3 functions and 1 constant.**\n   241вҶ’\n   242вҶ’### What is NOT changed:\n   243вҶ’- The dedup logic (DO NOT CHANGE directive respected)\n   244вҶ’- The structural heading selection\n   245вҶ’- The scoring formula or bonuses\n   246вҶ’- The bilingual detection logic (its false trigger is prevented by the breadcrumb filter upstream)\n   247вҶ’- The multi-title guard\n   248вҶ’- The capsCoalesced merge pass (working correctly)\n   249вҶ’- Any embedding or similarity logic\n   250вҶ’\n   251вҶ’### Expected accuracy: 11/11 (100%)\n   252вҶ’- KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA: breadcrumb filtered вҶ’ real title not suppressed вҶ’ wins (**fixed**)\n   253вҶ’- LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS: `BALLS` suppressed as metadata continuation вҶ’ merged title wins (**fixed**)\n   254вҶ’- SmaЕјona zielona fasolka: `DLA & OSOB` caught by expanded metadata pattern вҶ’ mixed-case title wins (**fixed**)\n   255вҶ’- All 8 previously passing recipes: no changes to their code paths (verified by safety analysis above)\n   256вҶ’\n   257вҶ’---\n   258вҶ’\n   259вҶ’## Testing Plan\n   260вҶ’\n   261вҶ’### New unit tests needed:\n   262вҶ’\n   263вҶ’1. **Breadcrumb filter:** Input starting with `/ Section / Subsection\\nREAL TITLE\\n...`. Expected: `REAL TITLE` (breadcrumb filtered).\n   264вҶ’\n   265вҶ’2. **Mid-word casing garble:** Input where only non-garbled candidates should survive after `UuIw` or `aBc` type lines are present. Expected: garbled lines do not win.\n   266вҶ’\n   267вҶ’3. **Metadata continuation suppression:** Input with `MAKES 25 SOMETHING\\nWORD\\n<body>` where `WORD` appears in the title. Expected: `WORD` does not enter the candidate pool; the full title wins.\n   268вҶ’\n   269вҶ’4. **OCR-corrupted DLA pattern:** Input containing `DLA & OSOB` and a mixed-case title. Expected: mixed-case title wins; `DLA & OSOB` filtered as metadata.\n   270вҶ’\n   271вҶ’### Regression tests (existing, must still pass):\n   272вҶ’- All 20 existing `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` tests in `title-extractor.test.ts`\n   273вҶ’- Full corpus run via `title-loop.py` against all 11 real input files + 102 generated inputs\n   274вҶ’\n   275вҶ’### Edge cases to verify manually:\n   276вҶ’- `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` вҖ” single slash, must NOT be filtered by breadcrumb rule\n   277вҶ’- `TITLE FIRST PART / SECOND PART` вҖ” single slash, must NOT be filtered\n   278вҶ’- Continuation merge still works for lines starting with `/` when preceded by another line\n   279вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014867ti9qiG3i71fZNmJ1wr","session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"fd2bcf30-4118-4e5b-85c5-114f3a773882"}
