{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014Ha3mbHXovv45fkwEJxNag","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Iteration 15 вҖ” Improvement Plan\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’## Overview\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’Two failures, two distinct root causes, but a shared theme: the algorithm's structural-heading machinery is too rigid for OCR layouts that deviate from the \"single ALL_CAPS line = title\" assumption. The fixes below are targeted but non-trivial вҖ” each addresses a design gap rather than patching a symptom.\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’**Accuracy trajectory:** 14 вҶ’ 81.8% (regression from 98.1% at iter 13, caused by corpus expansion to 11 recipes exposing pre-existing gaps). The two failures here are new test cases, not regressions.\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’---\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’## Failure 1: LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’**Expected:** `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS`\n    14вҶ’**Got:** `WITH NIGELLA + SEEDS`\n    15вҶ’\n    16вҶ’### Root Cause Analysis\n    17вҶ’\n    18вҶ’Two compounding issues:\n    19вҶ’\n    20вҶ’1. **3-line join ceiling** вҖ” The title spans 4 OCR lines (`LABANEH` / `BALLS` / `WITH NIGELLA` / `SEEDS`). `buildCandidates` generates joins of up to 3 consecutive lines, so the full title is never in the candidate pool. The best candidate covering the start is the 3-line join `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA` (position 0).\n    21вҶ’\n    22вҶ’2. **Dedup \"shorter wins\" destroys the 3-line join** вҖ” `WITH NIGELLA` (single, position 2) is a substring of `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA`. The dedup rule keeps the shorter form, eliminating the only candidate that captures the dish name. After dedup, only `WITH NIGELLA` and `SEEDS` survive, producing `WITH NIGELLA + SEEDS`.\n    23вҶ’\n    24вҶ’The existing continuation-character pre-merge (`/^[/&+:(]/`) doesn't help because `BALLS`, `WITH NIGELLA`, and `SEEDS` don't start with continuation punctuation вҖ” they're just OCR-fragmented words of a single heading.\n    25вҶ’\n    26вҶ’### Proposed Fix: Short ALL_CAPS Line Merge Pass\n    27вҶ’\n    28вҶ’Add a **pre-processing pass** in `buildCandidates`, before the existing continuation-character merge, that collapses consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines into single logical lines. The insight: when a recipe page has a sequence of 2+ consecutive ALL_CAPS lines where each line has вүӨ2 words and вүӨ25 characters, they are almost certainly fragments of a single heading broken by OCR line detection.\n    29вҶ’\n    30вҶ’**Algorithm:**\n    31вҶ’\n    32вҶ’```\n    33вҶ’Input lines (after burst skip):\n    34вҶ’  LABANEH           (ALL_CAPS, 1 word, 7 chars)\n    35вҶ’  BALLS             (ALL_CAPS, 1 word, 5 chars)\n    36вҶ’  WITH NIGELLA      (ALL_CAPS, 2 words, 12 chars)\n    37вҶ’  SEEDS             (ALL_CAPS, 1 word, 5 chars)\n    38вҶ’  Essential to...   (mixed-case, long вҖ” breaks the run)\n    39вҶ’\n    40вҶ’After short-caps merge:\n    41вҶ’  LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS   (merged, position 0)\n    42вҶ’  Essential to...                     (unchanged)\n    43вҶ’```\n    44вҶ’\n    45вҶ’**Merge criteria for each line in the run:**\n    46вҶ’- `isAllCaps(line)` is true\n    47вҶ’- `wordCount(line) <= 2`\n    48вҶ’- `line.length <= 25`\n    49вҶ’- NOT a section label (`isSectionLabel` returns false)\n    50вҶ’- NOT a metadata line (`looksLikeMetadata` returns false)\n    51вҶ’\n    52вҶ’**Run termination:** The run breaks when a line fails any criterion, or is empty, or when the accumulated merged text exceeds 80 characters (the existing `passesHardFilters` length cap).\n    53вҶ’\n    54вҶ’**Where in the code:** In `buildCandidates`, after the `burstEnd` computation and before the continuation-character pre-merge loop. The merged lines feed into the existing continuation merge and candidate generation unchanged.\n    55вҶ’\n    56вҶ’**Before:**\n    57вҶ’```typescript\n    58вҶ’// Pre-merge continuation lines: a line starting with /&+:( ...\n    59вҶ’const mergedLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n    60вҶ’for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n    61вҶ’```\n    62вҶ’\n    63вҶ’**After:**\n    64вҶ’```typescript\n    65вҶ’// Pre-merge consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (OCR-fragmented headings)\n    66вҶ’const capsCoalesced: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n    67вҶ’let i = burstEnd;\n    68вҶ’while (i < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n    69вҶ’  const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n    70вҶ’  if (\n    71вҶ’    isAllCaps(line.text) &&\n    72вҶ’    wordCount(line.text) <= 2 &&\n    73вҶ’    line.text.length <= 25 &&\n    74вҶ’    !isSectionLabel(line.text) &&\n    75вҶ’    !looksLikeMetadata(line.text)\n    76вҶ’  ) {\n    77вҶ’    // Start a run of short ALL_CAPS lines\n    78вҶ’    let merged = line.text;\n    79вҶ’    const startIndex = line.index;\n    80вҶ’    let j = i + 1;\n    81вҶ’    while (j < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n    82вҶ’      const next = nonEmptyLines[j];\n    83вҶ’      if (\n    84вҶ’        isAllCaps(next.text) &&\n    85вҶ’        wordCount(next.text) <= 2 &&\n    86вҶ’        next.text.length <= 25 &&\n    87вҶ’        !isSectionLabel(next.text) &&\n    88вҶ’        !looksLikeMetadata(next.text) &&\n    89вҶ’        (merged + \" \" + next.text).length <= 80\n    90вҶ’      ) {\n    91вҶ’        merged += \" \" + next.text;\n    92вҶ’        j++;\n    93вҶ’      } else {\n    94вҶ’        break;\n    95вҶ’      }\n    96вҶ’    }\n    97вҶ’    if (j > i + 1) {\n    98вҶ’      // Merged 2+ lines into one\n    99вҶ’      capsCoalesced.push({ text: merged, index: startIndex });\n   100вҶ’      i = j;\n   101вҶ’      continue;\n   102вҶ’    }\n   103вҶ’  }\n   104вҶ’  capsCoalesced.push(line);\n   105вҶ’  i++;\n   106вҶ’}\n   107вҶ’\n   108вҶ’// Pre-merge continuation lines: a line starting with /&+:( ...\n   109вҶ’const mergedLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   110вҶ’for (let k = 0; k < capsCoalesced.length; k++) {\n   111вҶ’  // (rest of existing logic, but iterating over capsCoalesced instead of nonEmptyLines starting at burstEnd)\n   112вҶ’```\n   113вҶ’\n   114вҶ’**Why this works:**\n   115вҶ’- `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` enters the pool as a single candidate at position 0.\n   116вҶ’- It qualifies as a structural heading (ALL_CAPS, 5 significant words вүҘ4 letters).\n   117вҶ’- No substring fragment can beat it in dedup because the full title is a single candidate now.\n   118вҶ’- The 3-line join ceiling becomes irrelevant for this case вҖ” the problem is solved at the source.\n   119вҶ’\n   120вҶ’**Safety considerations:**\n   121вҶ’- The merge only fires for ALL_CAPS short lines. Mixed-case lines (which could be separate paragraphs) are never merged.\n   122вҶ’- Section labels like `INGREDIENTS` or `SKЕҒADNIKI` break the run, preventing \"TITLE INGREDIENTS NEXT_TITLE\" merges.\n   123вҶ’- The 80-char cap matches `passesHardFilters` and prevents runaway merges of many short lines.\n   124вҶ’- Existing tests: `ARAYES\\nSHRAK` (2 short ALL_CAPS lines) should still work вҖ” they'll be merged into `ARAYES SHRAK` even earlier, which is the correct result. The `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` + `FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` test has multi-word (>2 word) lines and body text between them, so no merge fires.\n   125вҶ’\n   126вҶ’**Potential concern вҖ” CHLEBEK test:**\n   127вҶ’```\n   128вҶ’CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM    (5 words вҖ” too many for merge)\n   129вҶ’WARZYWA I BOCZEK                  (3 words вҖ” too many for merge)\n   130вҶ’```\n   131вҶ’Both lines have >2 words, so they don't trigger the short-caps merge. Safe.\n   132вҶ’\n   133вҶ’---\n   134вҶ’\n   135вҶ’## Failure 2: SmaЕјona zielona fasolka\n   136вҶ’\n   137вҶ’**Expected:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`\n   138вҶ’**Got:** `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM`\n   139вҶ’\n   140вҶ’### Root Cause Analysis\n   141вҶ’\n   142вҶ’Two compounding issues:\n   143вҶ’\n   144вҶ’1. **Structural bonus inaccessible to mixed-case titles** вҖ” `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` is the correct title at position 0 (mixed-case, Polish convention). `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` at position 1 (ALL_CAPS, English+Korean romanization) receives the +0.08 ALL_CAPS bonus and +0.10 structural heading bonus, pushing it above the Polish title.\n   145вҶ’\n   146вҶ’2. **Bilingual detection threshold too strict** вҖ” The guard at lines 451-472 checks whether the position-0 mixed-case candidate and a nearby ALL_CAPS candidate have cosine similarity > 0.4. For Polish вҶ” Korean romanization (\"BORKEUM\" = лі¶мқҢ = stir-fry), MiniLM embeddings can't reliably achieve 0.4 because the word roots are completely unrelated across these language families.\n   147вҶ’\n   148вҶ’### Proposed Fix: Position-Based Bilingual Layout Detection\n   149вҶ’\n   150вҶ’Replace the embedding-similarity bilingual guard with a **layout-based heuristic** that doesn't depend on cross-lingual semantic similarity at all. The key insight: in multilingual cookbooks, the layout is deterministic:\n   151вҶ’\n   152вҶ’```\n   153вҶ’Line 0: Primary title (native language, often mixed-case)\n   154вҶ’Line 1: Translation / romanization (often ALL_CAPS)\n   155вҶ’Line 2: Second script / additional translation (often filtered by garbled check)\n   156вҶ’```\n   157вҶ’\n   158вҶ’When this layout is detected, the position-0 candidate should be strongly preferred regardless of embedding similarity between the two title forms.\n   159вҶ’\n   160вҶ’**New heuristic вҖ” `isBilingualHeader`:**\n   161вҶ’\n   162вҶ’The existing bilingual guard (lines 451-472) should be expanded with a second, independent trigger condition:\n   163вҶ’\n   164вҶ’```\n   165вҶ’Trigger condition (NEW вҖ” layout-based, no embedding similarity required):\n   166вҶ’  1. There exists a mixed-case candidate at position 0 with wordCount вүҘ 2\n   167вҶ’  2. There exists an ALL_CAPS candidate at position 1 or 2 with wordCount вүҘ 2\n   168вҶ’  3. The mixed-case candidate at position 0 does NOT look like a section label\n   169вҶ’  4. The ALL_CAPS candidate is NOT a structural section label\n   170вҶ’  5. The two candidates share NO words in common (cross-lingual indicator вҖ”\n   171вҶ’     same-language titles like \"Pierogi Ruskie\" / \"PIEROGI RUSKIE\" would share words)\n   172вҶ’```\n   173вҶ’\n   174вҶ’When triggered, suppress the ALL_CAPS candidate from `scoredForThreshold` (same as current bilingual guard behavior), preventing its bonuses from inflating the threshold and ensuring the mixed-case position-0 title wins.\n   175вҶ’\n   176вҶ’**Before (existing guard):**\n   177вҶ’```typescript\n   178вҶ’let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n   179вҶ’const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n   180вҶ’if (prePos0) {\n   181вҶ’  const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n   182вҶ’    (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2\n   183вҶ’  );\n   184вҶ’  const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n   185вҶ’  if (pos0Embedding && nearbyAllCaps.length > 0) {\n   186вҶ’    const translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n   187вҶ’      const capEmbedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === cap.text)?.embedding;\n   188вҶ’      if (!capEmbedding) return false;\n   189вҶ’      return cosineSimilarity(pos0Embedding, capEmbedding) > 0.4;\n   190вҶ’    });\n   191вҶ’    // ... suppress translationCandidates\n   192вҶ’  }\n   193вҶ’}\n   194вҶ’```\n   195вҶ’\n   196вҶ’**After (layout-based fallback added):**\n   197вҶ’```typescript\n   198вҶ’let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n   199вҶ’const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n   200вҶ’if (prePos0) {\n   201вҶ’  const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n   202вҶ’    (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2\n   203вҶ’      && s.origin === \"single\"  // only single-line ALL_CAPS, not joins\n   204вҶ’  );\n   205вҶ’  const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n   206вҶ’\n   207вҶ’  let translationCandidates: typeof nearbyAllCaps = [];\n   208вҶ’\n   209вҶ’  // Method 1: embedding similarity (existing вҖ” works for related languages)\n   210вҶ’  if (pos0Embedding && nearbyAllCaps.length > 0) {\n   211вҶ’    translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n   212вҶ’      const capEmbedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === cap.text)?.embedding;\n   213вҶ’      if (!capEmbedding) return false;\n   214вҶ’      return cosineSimilarity(pos0Embedding, capEmbedding) > 0.4;\n   215вҶ’    });\n   216вҶ’  }\n   217вҶ’\n   218вҶ’  // Method 2: layout-based detection (NEW вҖ” works for distant languages)\n   219вҶ’  // If embedding similarity didn't find translations, check layout:\n   220вҶ’  // mixed-case вүҘ2 words at pos 0 + ALL_CAPS вүҘ2 words at pos 1-2 sharing no words\n   221вҶ’  if (translationCandidates.length === 0 && wordCount(prePos0.text) >= 2) {\n   222вҶ’    const pos0Words = new Set(\n   223вҶ’      prePos0.text.toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/).filter(w => w.length > 2)\n   224вҶ’    );\n   225вҶ’    translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n   226вҶ’      if (wordCount(cap.text) < 2) return false;\n   227вҶ’      const capWords = cap.text.toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/).filter(w => w.length > 2);\n   228вҶ’      // No significant words in common вҶ’ likely different languages\n   229вҶ’      const hasCommonWord = capWords.some(w => pos0Words.has(w));\n   230вҶ’      return !hasCommonWord;\n   231вҶ’    });\n   232вҶ’  }\n   233вҶ’\n   234вҶ’  if (translationCandidates.length > 0) {\n   235вҶ’    // (existing suppression logic, unchanged)\n   236вҶ’    scoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n   237вҶ’      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   238вҶ’      return !translationCandidates.some((t) => sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()));\n   239вҶ’    });\n   240вҶ’  }\n   241вҶ’}\n   242вҶ’```\n   243вҶ’\n   244вҶ’**Why this works for `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka`:**\n   245вҶ’- Position 0: `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` (mixed-case, 3 words)\n   246вҶ’- Position 1: `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` (ALL_CAPS, 3 words, single-line)\n   247вҶ’- No words in common (Polish vs English+Korean)\n   248вҶ’- Layout trigger fires вҶ’ `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` suppressed from threshold\n   249вҶ’- `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` wins on position\n   250вҶ’\n   251вҶ’**Why this is safe for existing tests:**\n   252вҶ’\n   253вҶ’- **Faszerowana papryka test:** Position 0 = `Faszerowana papryka` (mixed-case), Position 1 = `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM` (ALL_CAPS). Words: {faszerowana, papryka} vs {paprika, gyeran-jjim}. \"papryka\" vs \"paprika\" вҖ” these don't match exactly as strings. The layout guard fires and suppresses the ALL_CAPS line, which is the **already correct** behavior (previously achieved via embedding similarity). No regression.\n   254вҶ’\n   255вҶ’- **CHOCOLATE CAKE test:** `CHOCOLATE CAKE` is at position 0 and is itself ALL_CAPS, so `prePos0` (looking for mixed-case at position 0) is null. Guard doesn't fire. Safe.\n   256вҶ’\n   257вҶ’- **ARAYES SHRAK test:** Both lines are ALL_CAPS. No mixed-case at position 0. Guard doesn't fire. Safe.\n   258вҶ’\n   259вҶ’- **FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS test:** Both are ALL_CAPS. No mixed-case at position 0. Guard doesn't fire. Safe.\n   260вҶ’\n   261вҶ’- **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM test:** ALL_CAPS at position 0. No mixed-case at position 0. Guard doesn't fire. Safe.\n   262вҶ’\n   263вҶ’- **Pierogi Ruskie test:** Position 0 = `SkЕӮadniki` (section label, filtered by hard filters). Position 1 = `Pierogi Ruskie`. There's no mixed-case candidate at position 0 that passes filters. Guard doesn't fire. Safe.\n   264вҶ’\n   265вҶ’**Potential concern вҖ” false positives on single-language pages:**\n   266вҶ’Could a page have a mixed-case title at line 0 and a different ALL_CAPS recipe title at line 1? This would be unusual layout вҖ” recipe books don't typically put two different recipe titles on consecutive lines in the same language. The \"no words in common\" check provides additional safety: if the titles are in the same language, they'd likely share at least a preposition or article. But to be extra safe, we restrict this to `origin === \"single\"` for the ALL_CAPS candidates (not joins) since joins of disparate content could spuriously match.\n   267вҶ’\n   268вҶ’---\n   269вҶ’\n   270вҶ’## Summary of Changes\n   271вҶ’\n   272вҶ’| Change | Files | Risk | Impact |\n   273вҶ’|--------|-------|------|--------|\n   274вҶ’| Short ALL_CAPS line merge pass | `title-extractor.ts` (~30 lines in `buildCandidates`) | Low вҖ” only fires on вүӨ2 word ALL_CAPS lines | Fixes LABANEH; enables future 4+ line titles |\n   275вҶ’| Layout-based bilingual detection | `title-extractor.ts` (~15 lines in bilingual guard) | Low вҖ” fallback, only fires when embedding guard doesn't | Fixes SmaЕјona zielona fasolka; covers all language pairs |\n   276вҶ’\n   277вҶ’**Neither change modifies:**\n   278вҶ’- The dedup logic (explicitly warned not to change)\n   279вҶ’- The structural heading selection\n   280вҶ’- The scoring formula\n   281вҶ’- The multi-title guard\n   282вҶ’- Any hard filters\n   283вҶ’\n   284вҶ’**Expected accuracy:** 11/11 (100%) вҖ” both failures addressed without regressions to existing 9 passing cases.\n   285вҶ’\n   286вҶ’---\n   287вҶ’\n   288вҶ’## Testing Plan\n   289вҶ’\n   290вҶ’### New unit tests needed:\n   291вҶ’\n   292вҶ’1. **4-line ALL_CAPS title merge:** Input with `LABANEH\\nBALLS\\nWITH NIGELLA\\nSEEDS\\n<body text>`. Expected: `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS`.\n   293вҶ’\n   294вҶ’2. **Short-caps merge doesn't merge across section labels:** Input with `WORD ONE\\nINGREDIENTS\\nWORD TWO`. Expected: merge does NOT happen (INGREDIENTS breaks the run).\n   295вҶ’\n   296вҶ’3. **Short-caps merge respects word-count limit:** Input with `THREE WORD LINE\\nANOTHER LINE`. Expected: no merge (first line has 3 words, exceeds вүӨ2 limit).\n   297вҶ’\n   298вҶ’4. **Layout bilingual detection with no shared words:** Input with `Mixed Case Title\\nALL CAPS DIFFERENT\\n<body>`. Expected: mixed-case title wins.\n   299вҶ’\n   300вҶ’5. **Layout bilingual detection skipped when words overlap:** Input with `Apple Pie Recipe\\nAPPLE PIE DELUXE\\n<body>`. Expected: normal scoring (shared words \"apple\", \"pie\" prevent bilingual suppression).\n   301вҶ’\n   302вҶ’### Regression tests (existing, must still pass):\n   303вҶ’- All 15 existing `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` tests in `title-extractor.test.ts`\n   304вҶ’- Full corpus run via `title-loop.py` against all 11 input files\n   305вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014867ti9qiG3i71fZNmJ1wr","session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"a779db82-65ff-4af6-853d-b725dbb55bdf"}
