t failed:** Files starting with 28вҖ“35 lines of repeated cooking instruction fragments (e.g., \"Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form\") beat the actual recipe title.\n- **Why:** `findBurstEnd` only skips short garbled lines (<20 chars). Generated test files have long (30вҖ“55 char) instruction preambles that pass hard filters.\n- **Impact:** Second-largest cluster; specific to generated corpus structure.\n- **Attempted fix:** Change 5 (Iter 19 plan) вҖ” add `looksLikeCookingInstruction()` filter + enhanced burst detection; rejects lines starting with imperative cooking verbs.\n\n#### **3. Bilingual/Translation Handling Issues**\n- **Iter 16 failure:** Trilingual input (Polish + English + Korean) produced corrupted joins containing translation text. Polish title lost.\n  - **Fix:** Extend bilingual suppression to catch embedded translations (suffixes/includes, not just prefixes).\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 17 improvement plan.\n\n- **Iter 17 failure:** ALL_CAPS category footer (WARZYWA = \"vegetables\") beats title due to position factor & ALL_CAPS bonus.\n  - **Root:** SECTION_LABELS missing Polish food-category words.\n  - **Fix:** Expand SECTION_LABELS + position-aware single-ALL_CAPS guard + reduce bonus for single-word ALL_CAPS.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 18; then regressed in Iter 19.\n\n- **Iter 15 failure:** Breadcrumb at position 0 (`/ Jesien / Zupy`) triggers false bilingual detection, suppresses real title.\n  - **Root:** `prePos0` heuristic assumes any mixed-case line at position 0 is a title; forward-slash breadcrumbs evade pipe filter.\n  - **Fix:** Add breadcrumb filter (2+ slashes) + mid-word casing check.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 16.\n\n#### **4. ALL_CAPS Structural Bonus Misfires**\n- **Iter 14 failure:** Mixed-case Polish title loses to ALL_CAPS English translation due to +0.10 structural bonus (inaccessible to non-ALL_CAPS).\n  - **Fix:** Layout-based bilingual detection (Method 2) вҖ” doesn't rely on embedding similarity; works for distant language pairs.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 15 improvement plan; implemented alongside short-caps merge.\n\n- **Iter 15 failure:** `UuIw` (OCR garbage) escapes garbled filter because it has 4 letters (threshold вүӨ3) and vowel ratio 0.75 (in range).\n  - **Fix:** Add mid-word casing check (`[a-z][A-Z]` pattern = OCR noise).\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 16.\n\n- **Iter 18 failures:** Many ALL_CAPS vs. Title Case mismatches. Plus, ALL_CAPS metadata lines (e.g., corrupted `DLA & OSOB`) beat mixed-case titles.\n  - **Fix:** Case normalization + OCR-resilient metadata patterns.\n  - **Status:** Planned in Iter 19 improvement plan.\n\n#### **5. Dedup \"Shorter Wins\" Destroys Multi-Line Joins**\n- **Iter 14 failure:** 4-line title split across lines, only 3-line join generated. Dedup removes join because `WITH NIGELLA` (substring, shorter) survives as standalone.\n  - **Root:** Join not protected from component-part dedup.\n  - **Fix:** Short ALL_CAPS line merge pass (capsCoalesced) вҖ” pre-merge fragmented ALL_CAPS before candidate generation.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 15; now part of standard pipeline.\n\n- **Iter 18 failures:** Split-title cases (Lamb Stew, Е»ur Е»ytni) where single-word components destroy multi-word joins.\n  - **Fix:** Change 3 (Iter 19) вҖ” protect joins from component singles when all parts survived threshold.\n  - **Status:** Planned but not fully detailed in iter 18 analysis.\n\n#### **6. Metadata Fragment Pollution**\n- **Iter 15 failure:** `MAKES 25 LABANEH BALLS` вҶ’ `MAKES 25 LABANEH` filtered, but `BALLS` survives as orphan and destroys merged title in dedup.\n  - **Fix:** Metadata continuation suppression вҖ” skip ALL_CAPS short lines immediately following metadata.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 16.\n\n- **Iter 18 failures:** Single-character OCR corruption (4 вҶ’ &) defeats metadata regex; serves as title.\n  - **Example:** `DLA & OSOB` (should be `DLA 4 OSГ“B`).\n  - **Fix:** OCR-resilient patterns; expand to accept non-digit serving-size structures.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 16 improvement plan.\n\n#### **7. Section Label & Category Word Misidentification**\n- **Iter 16 failure:** Diacritic-stripped section labels bypass filter. OCR `SKLADNIKI` doesn't match stored `SKЕҒADNIKI`.\n  - **Fix:** Diacritic-insensitive matching.\n  - **Status:** Fixed in Iter 17 improvement plan.\n\n- **Iter 18 failure:** `Zupy` (category word in SECTION_LABELS) blocks 3-line join for title `Zupy Zimowe Warzywne`.\n  - **Root:** Join-blocking rule too broad; doesn't account for multi-word titles starting with a category word.\n  - **Fix:** Relax section-label join block when result has вүҘ3 words.\n  - **Status:** Planned in Iter 19 improvement plan.\n\n#### **8. Page Number Prefixes**\n- **Iter 18 failure:** `34  Berry Jam` вҶ’ startsWithNumber filter rejects entire line; title never appears.\n  - **Fix:** Strip page number prefix before hard filtering.\n  - **Status:** Planned in Iter 19 improvement plan.\n\n#### **9. Parenthetical English Glosses Over-Merged**\n- **Iter 18 failures:** Continuation merge includes `(Polish Gingerbread)` gloss in title.\n  - **Examples:** `PIEROGI RUSKIE (Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)`.\n  - **Fix:** Strip parenthetical glosses when mixing ALL_CAPS base + mixed-case parenthetical.\n  - **Status:** Planned in Iter 19 improvement plan.\n\n#### **10. Compound Title Substring Collisions**\n- **Iter 18 failure:** `HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION` (line 1) vs `DILL SAUCE VARIATION` (line 32, sub-recipe header). Dedup keeps shorter.\n  - **Fix:** Position-aware dedup вҖ” protect position-0 compound titles from distant sub-headers.\n  - **Status:** Planned in Iter 19 improvement plan.\n\n---\n\n### **Recurring Themes & Patterns**\n\n#### **Theme 1: OCR Corruption Defeats Focused Filters**\n- Single-character errors (`4вҶ’&`, `ЕӮвҶ’l`, diacritics) defeat narrow regex patterns.\n- **Solution trajectory:** Move from narrow patterns to broader OCR-resilient checks (e.g., `[^a-zA-Z0-9]` for non-alphanumeric tokens).\n\n#### **Theme 2: All-Caps Bonus System Amplifies Non-Titles**\n- By design, ALL_CAPS lines get +0.08 bonus + possible +0.10 structural bonus (total +0.18).\n- **Fails when:** Real title is mixed-case (Polish, Italian conventions) or is body text/metadata in ALL_CAPS.\n- **Cascading fixes:**\n  - Iter 17: Add category labels to SECTION_LABELS.\n  - Iter 17: Reduce single-word ALL_CAPS bonus from +0.08 to +0.03.\n  - Iter 17: Position-aware guard for ALL_CAPS in last 25% of document.\n\n#### **Theme 3: Bilingual Detection Too Rigid**\n- Embedding similarity threshold (0.4) fails for distant language families (Polish вҶ” Korean romanization).\n- **Solution:** Layered approach вҖ” Method 1 (embedding-based) + Method 2 (layout-based) with word-overlap check.\n\n#### **Theme 4: Multi-Line Join Fragility**\n- Title split across 4+ lines вҶ’ only 3-line joins possible вҶ’ dedup destroys join via component parts.\n- **Solution:** Pre-merge short ALL_CAPS fragments (capsCoalesced) before candidate generation, solving at source.\n\n#### **Theme 5: Hard Filter Coverage Gaps**\n- `isLikelyGarbled` misses: 4-letter words with mid-case transitions, non-ASCII single-word short-word check counts only ASCII.\n- `looksLikeMetadata` misses: OCR-corrupted variants (& for digit, missing diacritics).\n- **Solution:** Add specific checks (mid-case, Unicode letter count, OCR-resilient patterns).\n\n#### **Theme 6: No Post-Processing Normalization**\n- Algorithm returns text exactly as OCR produces it (casing, diacritics, etc.).\n- **Affects:** ~20 failures where content is correct but formatting is wrong.\n- **Solution:** Case normalization pass at output stage.\n\n---\n\n### **What Worked (Stable Across Iterations)**\n\n1. **Embedding-based scoring model** (rawScore formula) вҖ” never fundamentally changed; tuning was on bonuses/thresholds.\n2. **Hard filter framework** вҖ” robust; only needed gap-filling (new checks, not restructuring).\n3. **Multi-title guard logic** вҖ” correct concept; only needed refinement (position-awareness, positional tiebreaks).\n4. **Continuation character pre-merge** вҖ” reliable; short-caps merge (Iter 15) extended it successfully.\n5. **Structural heading selection** вҖ” works well for ALL_CAPS multi-word titles; issue is bilingual + bonus allocation, not the selection itself.\n\n---\n\n### **What Regressed or Required Revision**\n\n1. **Bilingual detection:** Initially embedding-only; extended to layout-based fallback (Iter 15). Changed focus from similarity threshold to document structure.\n2. **Dedup logic:** Marked \"DO NOT CHANGE\" but required upstream fixes (capsCoalesced, join protection, position-aware dedup guards) to prevent false positives.\n3. **ALL_CAPS bonuses:** Calibration changed multiple times (Iter 17 reduced single-word bonus; Iter 18/19 complexity from collateral effects).\n4. **commonShort2 expansion:** Iter 19 fix for Polish titles (Pattern 2, Iter 18) admitted Polish body text as candidates (Iter 19 regression on real files).\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Insights**\n\n1. **Defense-in-depth layers:** Filters at hard-filter stage, scoring stage, post-threshold stage, multi-title guard, dedup. A gap at any layer can cascade (e.g., breadcrumb bypassing hard filters вҶ’ bilingual false positive).\n\n2. **OCR fragility:** The algorithm is sound for clean OCR. Real-world OCR introduces: corrupted digits (`4вҶ’&`), missing diacritics, repeated preambles, mixed languages. Fixes are incremental (add patterns, add checks), not architectural.\n\n3. **Dedup as safety net, not primary control:** Dedup is \"shorter substring wins\" вҖ” correct for noise (`Pierogi Ruskie 200g mД…ki` вҶ’ `Pierogi Ruskie`) but breaks when shortersubstring is a **structural fragment** (not noise). Solution is upstream (prevent fragments entering pool), not changing dedup rule.\n\n4. **Bilingual complexity:** The layout-based detection (Method 2) is more robust than embedding-based for distant languages. But it only fires on `prePos0` (mixed-case position 0) + `nearbyAllCaps` (positions 1вҖ“2). If layout is different, guard misses.\n\n5. **Position as a signal:** Position-0 candidates almost never fail to be titles. Position >75% ALL_CAPS candidates are almost never titles (usually footers/categories). Leveraging positional structure improves robustness.\n\n---\n\n### **Unresolved or Accepted Limitations**\n\n1. **OCR character substitution** (CrГЁme BrГ»lГ©e вҶ’ CrГЁme BrГ»**1**Г©e) вҖ” requires OCR post-processing, not title extraction.\n2. **Missing OCR words** (preposition `z` absent entirely) вҖ” unfixable without external knowledge.\n3. **Rare all-CAPS single-word titles in last 25% of page** вҖ” Position guard (Iter 17) would incorrectly suppress these, but such cases are vanishingly rare in recipe books.\n\n---\n\n### **Current Status (Iter 19)**\n\n- **Real files:** 10/11 pass (90.9%). One regression (SmaЕјona zielona fasolka) due to collateral effect of Polish preposition expansion.\n- **Root cause:** `commonShort2` fix (Iter 18 Pattern 2) now admits Polish body text. Needs either (a) extend `looksLikeCookingInstruction` to Polish verbs, or (b) position-based tiebreak for zero-ALL_CAPS results.\n- **Planned fixes in Iter 19 improvement plan:** 9 changes covering 48вҖ“52 of 54 generated-file failures; expected final accuracy ~96вҖ“98% on combined corpus."}],"totalDurationMs":60110,"totalTokens":119145,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2367,"cache_read_input_tokens":113037,"output_tokens":3736,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2367},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
