{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VqJBiofkMQ3BqDUVbWyuv7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me outline my thinking on the single failure, then write the improvement plan.\n\n**The failure:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` вҖ” Polish body-text lines (`Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno`) now pass hard filters because `na` was added to `commonShort2`. These body-text lines enter scoring, and the multi-title guard's zero-ALL_CAPS path keeps all candidates.\n\n**Key insight:** The feedback proposes two fixes (Polish cooking verbs, or position-based tiebreak). But looking deeper, I think the position-based tiebreak for zero-ALL_CAPS multi-candidate results is the most robust and generalizable fix. It doesn't require enumerating Polish verbs and handles future regressions of this type. However, adding Polish cooking verbs to `looksLikeCookingInstruction` is also valuable as defense-in-depth.\n\nLet me also look at what the actual body-text lines look like more carefully and think about whether there are additional signals we can use."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8561,"cache_read_input_tokens":55123,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8561},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"d708b1a7-f809-4f41-bffd-ea2cad6f99f7"}
