{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Giaq25jakxdirArZ1bfvNd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/19-55b161b/improvement-plan.md`. Here's the summary:\n\n**Single failure:** `SmaЕјona zielona fasolka` вҖ” Polish body-text lines leak into candidates after the `commonShort2` expansion, and the multi-title guard's zero-ALL_CAPS path keeps everything.\n\n**Three proposed fixes (defense-in-depth):**\n\n1. **Polish cooking verbs in `looksLikeCookingInstruction`** вҖ” Add `Podawaj`, `Dodaj`, `SmaЕј`, `Gotuj`, etc. to a parallel regex. Directly filters the offending `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` line. Low risk because imperative verbs never start recipe titles (titles use adjectives/nouns like `SmaЕјona`, not `SmaЕј`).\n\n2. **Position-based tiebreak for zero-ALL_CAPS results** вҖ” The multi-title guard currently has a no-op path when no ALL_CAPS candidates survive. Change it to prefer the earliest candidate (with a 3-position tolerance for score-based tiebreaks). This is the most general fix вҖ” catches any body-text leakage regardless of language.\n\n3. **Word count filter (вүҘ8 words)** вҖ” Recipe titles rarely exceed 7 words. Long body-text lines (the 12-word cooking instruction on line 22) are filtered outright. Exception for lines containing ` + `, ` : `, or ` & ` separators (legitimate multi-title compounds).\n\nAny single change fixes the regression. Together they close the class of \"body text leaking into candidates\" failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5276,"cache_read_input_tokens":63684,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5276},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"170bdbf7-3568-4ea7-9b3d-3d7e36d78c47","uuid":"dc7c04f4-db59-4619-a281-a63df26b